  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (18104)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 10
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18104&sectionno=3&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No ^2[person] shall, after the commencement of this Act, begin to carry on any`
  line `class of insurance business in ^1[India] and no insurer carrying on any class of insurance business in`
  line `^1[India] shall, after the expiry of three months from the commencement of this Act, continue to carry on`
  line `any such business, unless he has obtained from the ^3[Authority] a certificate of registration ^4[for the`
  line `particular class of insurance business:]`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that in the case of an insurer who was carrying on any class of insurance business in`
  line `^1[India] at the commencement of this Act, failure to obtain a certificate of registration in accordance with`
  line `the requirements of this sub-clause shall not operate to invalidate any contract of insurance entered into`
  line `by him if before ^6[such date as may be fixed in this behalf by the Central Government by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette], he has obtained that certificate.]`
  line
  line `^7[Provided further that a person or insurer, as the case may be, carrying on any class of insurance`
  line `business in India, on or before the commencement of the Insurance Regulatory and Development`
  line `Authority Act, 1999, for which no registration certificate was necessary prior to such commencement,`
  line `may continue to do so for a period of three months from such commencement or, if he had made an`
  line `application for such registration within the said period of three months, till the disposal of such`
  line `application:`
  line
  line `Provided also that any certificate of registration, obtained immediately before the commencement of`
  line `the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999, shall be deemed to have been obtained`
  line `from the Authority in accordance with the provisions of this Act.]`
  line
  line `^8[(2) Every application for registration shall be made in such manner and shall be accompanied by`
  line `such documents as may be specified by the regulations.]`
  line
  line `^9[(2A) If, on receipt of an application for registration and after making such inquiry as he deems`
  line `fit, the ^3[Authority] is satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) the financial condition and the general character of management of the applicant are sound;`
  line
  line `(b) the volume of business likely to be available to, and the capital structure and earning`
  line `prospects of, the applicant will be adequate;`
  line
  line `(c) the interests of the general public will be served if the certificate of registration is granted to`
  line `the applicant in respect of the class or classes of insurance business specified in the application; and`
  line
  line `(d) the applicant has complied with the provisions of sections 2C, ^10[(5 and 31A)] and has fulfilled`
  line `all the requirements of this section applicable to him,`
  line
  line `the ^3[Authority] may register the applicant as an insurer and grant him a certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `^11[(2AA) The Authority shall give preference to register the applicant and grant him a certificate of`
  line `registration if such applicant agrees, in the form and manner as may be specified by the regulations made`
  line `by the Authority, to carry on the life insurance business or general insurance business for providing health`
  line `cover to individuals or group of individuals.]`
  line
  line `(2B) Where the ^3[Authority] refuses registration, shall record the reasons for such decision and shall`
  line `furnish a copy thereof to the applicant.`
  line
  line `^12[(2C) Any person aggrieved by the decision of the Authority refusing registration may, within thirty`
  line `days from the date on which a copy of the decision is received by him, appeal to the Securities Appellate`
  line Tribunal.]
  line
  line `^13* * * * *`
  line
  line `^14[(3) In the case of any insurer having joint venture with a person having its principal place of`
  line `business domiciled outside India or any insurer as defined in sub-clause (d) of clause (9) of section 2, the`
  line `Authority may withhold registration already made if it is satisfied that in the country in which such person`
  line `has been debarred by law or practice of that country to carry on insurance business.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority may suspend or cancel the registration of an insurer either wholly or in so far as it`
  line `relates to a particular class of insurance business, as the case may be,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the insurer fails, at any time, to comply with the provisions of section 64VA as to the excess`
  line `of the value of his assets over the amount of his liabilities, or`
  line
  line `(b) if the insurer is in liquidation or is adjudged as an insolvent, or`
  line
  line `(c) if the business or a class of the business of the insurer has been transferred to any person or`
  line `has been transferred to or amalgamated with the business of any other insurer without the approval of`
  line `the Authority, or`
  line
  line `(d) if the insurer makes default in complying with, or acts in contravention of, any requirement of`
  line `this Act or of any rule or any regulation or order made or, any direction issued thereunder, or`
  line
  line `(e) if the Authority has reason to believe that any claim upon the insurer arising in India under`
  line `any policy of insurance remains unpaid for three months after final judgment in regular court of law,`
  line or
  line
  line `(f) if the insurer carries on any business other than insurance business or any prescribed business,`
  line or
  line
  line `(g) if the insurer makes a default in complying with any direction issued or order made, as the`
  line `case may be, by the Authority under the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999`
  line `(41 of 1999), or`
  line
  line `(h) if the insurer makes a default in complying with, or acts in contravention of, any requirement`
  line `of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) or the General Insurance Business (Nationalisation)`
  line `Act, 1972 (57 of 1972) or the Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999) or the`
  line `Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002 (15 of 2002), or`
  line
  line `(i) if the insurer fails to pay the annual fee required under section 3A, or`
  line
  line `(j) if the insurer is convicted for an offence under any law for the time being in force, or`
  line
  line `(k) if the insurer being a co-operative society set up under the relevant State laws or, as the case`
  line `may be, the Multi-State Co-operative Societies Act, 2002 (39 of 2002), contravenes the provisions of`
  line `law as may be applicable to the insurer.`
  line
  line `(5) When the Authority suspends or cancels any registration under clause (a), clause (d), clause (e),`
  line `clause (f), clause (g) or clause (i) of sub-section (4), it shall give notice in writing to the insurer of its`
  line `decision, and the decision shall take effect on such date as it may specify in that behalf in the notice, such`
  line `date not being less than one month not more than two months from the date of the receipt of the notice in`
  line `the ordinary course of transmission.`
  line
  line `(5A) When the Authority suspends or cancels any registration under clause (b), (c), (j) or (k) of`
  line `sub-section (4), the suspension or cancellation, as the case may be, shall take effect on the date on which`
  line `notice of the order of suspension or cancellation is served on the insurer.]`
  line
  line `^15[(5B) When a registration is cancelled the insurer shall not, after the cancellation has taken effect,`
  line `enter into any new contracts of insurance, but all rights and liabilities in respect of contracts of insurance`
  line `entered into by him before such cancellation takes effect shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (5D), continue as if the cancellation had not taken place.]`
  line
  line `^16[(5C) Where a registration is suspended or cancelled under clause (a), clause (d), clause (e),`
  line `clause (f), clause (g) or clause (i) of sub-section (4), the Authority may at its discretion revive the`
  line `registration, if the insurer within six months from the date on which the suspension or cancellation took`
  line `effect complies with the provisions of section 64VA as to the excess of the value of his assets over the`
  line `amount of his liabilities or has had an application under sub-section (4) of section 3A accepted, or`
  line `satisfies the Authority that no claim upon him such as is referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (4)`
  line `remains unpaid or that he has complied with any requirement of this Act or the Insurance Regulatory and`
  line `Development Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999), or of any rule or any regulation, or any order made`
  line `thereunder or any direction issued under those Acts, or that he has ceased to carry on any business other`
  line `than insurance business or any prescribed business, as the case may be, and complies with any directions`
  line `which may be given to him by the Authority.]`
  line
  line `^17[(5D) Where ^18[the registration of an insurance company is cancelled under sub-section (4), the`
  line `^3[Authority] may,] after the expiry of six months from the date on which the cancellation took effect,`
  line `apply to the Court for an order to wind up the insurance company, or to wind up the affairs of the`
  line `company in respect of a class of insurance business, unless the registration of the insurance company has`
  line `been revived under sub-section (5C) or an application for winding up the company has been`
  line `already presented to the Court. The Court may proceed as if an application under this sub-section were an`
  line `application under sub-section (2) of section 53, or sub-section (1) of section 58, as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `^19[(5E) The Authority may, by order, suspend or cancel any registration in such manner as may be`
  line `determined by the regulations made by it:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order under this sub-section shall be made unless the person concerned has been`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
  line
  line `^20* * * * *`
  line
  line `^21[(7) The Authority may, on payment of such fee, not exceeding five thousand rupees, as may be`
  line `determined by the regulations, issue a duplicate certificate of registration to replace a certificate lost,`
  line `destroyed or mutilated, or in any other case where the Authority is of opinion that the issue of duplicate`
  line `certificate is necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
