  line
  line `7. The proviso ins. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 6, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 32 of 1965, s. 2 (w.e.f. 29-9-1965).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 6, for "5, 31A and 32" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 6, for sub-section (2C) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `13. Sub-section (2D) omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-sections (3), (4), (5) and (5A) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `15. Ins. by Act 20 of 1940, s. 3.`
  line
  line `16. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 6, for sub-section (5C) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `17. Ins. by Act 20 of 1940, s. 3.`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by Act 6 of 1946, s. 3, for certain words (w.e.f. 20-3-1946).`
  line
  line `19. Ins. by s. 30 and the First Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `20. Sub-section (6) omitted by Act 32 of 1965, s. 2 (w.e.f. 29-9-1965).`
  line
  line `21. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for sub-section (7) (19-4-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (18105)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 11
  title `Payment of annual fee by insurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 7, for section 3A (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18105&sectionno=3A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Payment of annual fee by insurer.-- (1) An insurer who has been granted a certificate of`
  line `registration under section 3 shall pay such annual fee to the Authority in such manner as may be specified`
  line `by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Any failure to deposit the annual fee shall render the certificate of registration liable to be`
  line cancelled.]
obj_root_law_sections_3_b:
  sectionId (18106)
  sectionNo 3B
  orderNo 12
  title `Certification of soundness of terms of life insurance business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18106&sectionno=3B&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content:
  string
  line `^2[3B. Certification of soundness of terms of life insurance business.-- If, when considering an`
  line `application for registration under section 3 or at any other time, it appears to the ^1[Authority] that the`
  line `assured rates, advantages, terms and conditions offered or to be offered in connection with life insurance`
  line `business are in any respect not workable or sound, it may require that a statement thereof shall be`
  line `submitted to an actuary appointed by the insurer for the purpose and approved by the ^1[Authority], and`
  line `may by order in writing further require the insurer to make within such time as may be specified in the`
  line `order such modifications in the said rates, advantages, terms or conditions, as the case may be, as the said`
  line `actuary may report to be necessary to enable him to certify that the said rates, advantages, terms and`
  line `conditions are workable and sound.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 6 of 1946, s. 4 (w.e.f. 20-3-1946).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (18107)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 13
  title `Minimum limits for annuities and other benefits secured by policies of life insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 8, for section 4 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18107&sectionno=4&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Minimum limits for annuities and other benefits secured by policies of life insurance. --The`
  line `insurer shall pay or undertake to pay on any policy of life insurance or a group policy issued, a minimum`
  line `annuity and other benefits as may be determined by regulations excluding any profit or bonus provided`
  line `that this shall not prevent an insurer from converting any policy into a paid-up policy of any value or`
  line `payment of surrender value of any amount.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (18108)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 14
  title `Restriction on name of insurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18108&sectionno=5&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) An insurer shall not be registered by a name identical with`
  line `that by which an insurer in existence is already registered, or so nearly resembling that name as to be calculated to deceive except when the insurer in existence is in the course of being dissolved and`
  line `signifies his consent to the ^1[Authority],`
  line
  line `(2) If an insurer, through inadvertence or otherwise, is without such consent as aforesaid registered by`
  line `a name identical with that by which an insurer already in existence whether previously registered or not is`
  line `carrying on business or so nearly resembling it as to be calculated to deceive, the first-mentioned insurer`
  line `shall, if called upon to do so by the ^1[Authority] on the application of the second-mentioned insurer,`
  line `change his name within a time to be fixed by the ^1[Authority]:`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000). Earlier it was substituted by Act 47`
  line `of 1950, s. 4, for "Superintendent of Insurance" (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
  line
  line `2. The provisos omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 9 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (3) omitted by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (18109)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 15
  title `Requirements as to capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for section 6 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18109&sectionno=6&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Requirement as to capital.--(1) No insurer not being an insurer as defined in sub-clause (d) of`
  line `clause (9) of section 2, carrying on the business of life insurance, general insurance, health insurance or`
  line `re-insurance in India or after the commencement of the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority`
  line `Act, 1999 (41 of 1999), shall be registered unless he has,--`
  line
  line `(i) a paid-up equity capital of rupees one hundred crore, in case of a person carrying on the`
  line `business of life insurance or general insurance; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a paid-up equity capital of rupees one hundred crore, in case of a person carrying on`
  line `exclusively the business of health insurance; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a paid-up equity capital of rupees two hundred crore, in case of a person carrying on`
  line `exclusively the business as a re-insurer:`
  line
  line `Provided that the insurer, may enhance the paid-up equity capital, as provided in this section in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) and the rules, regulations or directions issued`
  line `thereunder or any other law for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in determining the paid-up equity capital, any preliminary expenses incurred`
  line `in the formation and registration of any insurer as may be specified by the regulations made under`
  line `this Act, shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(2) No insurer, as defined in sub-clause (d) of clause (9) of section 2, shall be registered unless he has`
  line `net owned funds of not less than rupees five thousand crore.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (18110)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 16
  title `Requirements as to capital structure and voting rights and maintenance of registers beneficial owners of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18110&sectionno=6A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Requirements as to capital structure and voting rights and maintenance of registers of`
  line `beneficial owners of shares. --`
  line `^2[(1) No public company limited by shares having its registered office in`
  line `India, shall carry on life insurance business or general insurance business or health insurance business or`
  line `re-insurance business, unless it satisfies the following conditions, namely: --`
  line
  line `(i) that the capital of the company shall consist of equity shares each having a single face value`
  line `and such other form of capital, as may be specified by the regulations;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the voting rights of shareholders are restricted to equity shares;`
  line
  line `(iii) that, except during any period not exceeding one year allowed by the company for payment`
  line `of calls on shares, the paid-up amount is the same for all shares, whether existing or new:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions specified in this sub-section shall not apply to a public company`
  line `which has, before the commencement of the Insurance (Amendment) Act, 1950 (47 of 1950), issued`
  line `any shares other than ordinary shares each of which has a single face value or any shares, the paid-up`
  line `amount whereof is not the same for all of them for a period of three years from such commencement.]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law for the time being in force or in`
  line `the memorandum or articles of association but subject to the other provisions contained in this section the`
  line `voting right of every shareholder of any public company as aforesaid shall in all cases be strictly`
  line `proportionate to the paid-up amount of the ^3[equity] shares held by him.`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `^5[(4) A public company as aforesaid which carries on life insurance business, general and health`
  line `insurance business and re-insurance business--`
  line
  line `(a) shall, in addition to the register of members maintained under the Companies Act, 2013`
  line `(18 of 2013), maintain a register of shares in which the name, occupation and address of the`
  line `beneficial owner of each share shall be entered including any change of beneficial owner declared to`
  line `it within fourteen days from the receipt of such declaration;`
  line
  line `(b) shall not register any transfer of its shares--`
  line
  line `(i) unless, in addition to compliance being made with the provisions of section 56 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), the transferee furnishes a declaration in the prescribed form`
  line `as to whether he proposes to hold the shares for his own benefit or as a nominee, whether jointly`
  line `or severally, on behalf of others and in the latter case giving the name, occupation and address of`
  line `the beneficial owner or owners, and the extent of the beneficial interest of each;`
  line
  line `(ii) where, after the transfer, the total paid-up holding of the transferee in the shares of the`
  line `company is likely to exceed five per cent. of its paid-up capital unless the previous approval of`
  line `the Authority has been obtained to the transfer;`
  line
  line `(iii) where, the nominal value of the shares intended to be transferred by any individual, firm,`
  line `group, constituents of a group, or body corporate under the same management, jointly or`
  line `severally exceeds one per cent. of the paid-up equity capital of the insurer, unless the previous`
  line `approval of the Authority has been obtained for the transfer.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-clause, the expressions "group" and "same`
  line `management" shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Competition Act,`
  line `2002 (12 of 2003).]`
  line
  line `(5) Every person who has any interest in any share of a company referred to in sub-section (4) which`
  line `stands in the name of another person in the register of members of the company, shall, within thirty days`
  line `from the commencement of the Insurance (Amendment) Act, 1950, or from the date on which he acquires`
  line `such interest, whichever is later, make a declaration in the prescribed form (which shall be countersigned`
  line `by the person in whose name the shares is registered) to the company declaring his interest in such share,`
  line `and notwithstanding anything contained in any other law or in any contract to the contrary, a person who`
  line `fails to make a declaration as aforesaid in respect of any share shall be deemed to have no right or title`
  line `whatsoever in that share:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall affect the right of a person who has an interest in any`
  line `such share to establish in a Court his right thereto, if the person, in whose name the share is registered,`
  line `refuses to countersign the declaration as required by this sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where any share, belonging to an individual who has made any such declaration`
  line `as is referred to in this sub-section is held by a company in its name in pursuance of any trust or for the`
  line `purpose of safe custody or collection or realisation of dividend, such individual shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913) or in the memorandum or articles of`
  line `association of the company which has issued the share, be deemed to be the holder of the said share for`
  line `the purpose of exercising any voting rights under this section to the exclusion of any other person.`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `^7* * * * *`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `^9* * * * *`
  line
  line `^10* * * * *`
  line
  line `^11[(11) The provisions of this section, ^12***, shall, on and from, the commencement of the Insurance`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1968, also apply to insurers carrying on general insurance business subject to the`
  line `following modifications, namely: --`
  line
  line `(i) that references in sub-sections (1), (3), (5) and (6) to the Insurance (Amendment) Act, 1950,`
  line `shall be construed as references to the Insurance (Amendment) Act, 1968; ^13***`
  line
  line `^14* * * * *`
  line
  line `^15[Explanation] --For the purpose of this section, the holding of a person in the shares of a company`
  line `shall be deemed to include--`
  line
  line `(i) the total paid-up holding in such shares held by such person in the name of others; and`
  line
  line `(ii) if any shares of the company are held--`
  line
  line `(a) by a public limited company, of which such person is a member holding more than ten`
  line `per cent of the paid-up capital, or`
  line
  line `(b) by a private limited company, of which such person is a member, or`
  line
  line `(c) by a company, of which such person is a managing director, manager, ^16*** or in which he`
  line `has a controlling interest, or`
  line
  line `(d) by a firm in which such person is a partner, or`
  line
  line `(e) by such person jointly with others,`
  line
  line `such part of the total paid-up holding of the company or firm or of the total joint holding in those shares,`
  line `as is proportionate to the contribution made by such person to the paid-up capital of the company, the`
  line `paid-up capital of the firm or the joint holding, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^17* * * * *`
