obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (18117)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 23
  title `Separation of accounts and funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18117&sectionno=10&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the insurer carries on business of more than`
  line `one of the ^1[following classes, namely, life insurance, fire insurance, marine insurance or miscellaneous`
  line `insurance], he shall keep a separate account of all receipts and payments in respect of each such class of`
  line `insurance business ^2[and where the insurer carries on business of ^3[miscellaneous insurance] whether`
  line `alone or in conjunction with business of another class, he shall, unless the ^4[Authority] waives this`
  line `requirement in writing, keep a separate account of all receipts and payments in respect of ^5[each of such`
  line `sub-classes of miscellaneous insurance business] as may be ^6[specified by the regulations]:`
  line
  line `Provided that no sub-class of ^7[miscellaneous insurance business] shall be prescribed under this`
  line `sub-section if the insurance business comprised in the sub-class consist of insurance contracts which are`
  line `terminable by the insurer at intervals not exceeding twelve months and under which, if a claim arises, the`
  line `insurer's liability to pay benefit ceases within one year of the date on which the claim arose.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where the insurer carries on the business of life insurance ^8[all receipts due in respect of such`
  line `business], shall be carried to and shall form a separate fund to be called the life insurance fund ^9[the`
  line `assets of which shall, ^10***, be kept distinct and separate from all other assets of the insurer] and the`
  line `deposit made by the insurer in respect of life insurance business shall be deemed to be ^11[part of the assets`
  line `of such fund; ^12[and every insurer shall, within the time limited in sub-section (1) of section 15 in regard`
  line `to the furnishing of the statements and accounts referred to in section 11, furnish to the Controller a`
  line `statement showing in detail such assets as at the close of every calendar year duly certified by an auditor`
  line `or by a person qualified to audit ^13***:]`
  line
  line `Provided that such statement shall, in the case of an insurer to whom section 11 applies, be set out as`
  line `a part of the balance-sheet mentioned in clause (a) of sub-section (I) of that section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an insurer may show in such statement all the assets held in his life department,`
  line `but at the same time showing any deductions on account of general reserves and other liabilities of that`
  line `department:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the ^14[Authority] may call for a statement similarly certified of such assets as at any`
  line `other date specified by him to be furnished within a period of three months from the date with reference`
  line `to which the statement is called for]].`
  line
  line `^15[(2A) No insurer carrying on life insurance business shall be entitled to be registered for any class of`
  line `insurance business in addition to the class or classes for which he has been already registered unless`
  line `the ^14[Authority] is satisfied that the assets of the life insurance fund of the insurer are adequate to meet`
  line `all his liabilities on policies of life insurance maturing for payment.]`
  line
  line `^16[(2AA) Where the insurer carries on the business of insurance, all receipts due in respect of each`
  line `sub-class of such insurance business shall be carried to and shall form a separate fund, the assets of which`
  line `shall be kept separate and distinct from other assets of the insurer and every insurer shall submit to the`
  line `Authority the necessary details of such funds as may be required by the Authority from time to time and`
  line `such funds shall not be applied directly or indirectly, save as expressly permitted under this Act or`
  line `regulations made thereunder.]`
  line
  line `(3) The life insurance fund shall be as absolutely the security of the life policy-holders as though it`
  line `belonged to an insurer carrying on no other business than life insurance business and shall not be liable`
  line `for any contracts of the insurer for which it would not have been liable had the business of the insurer`
  line `been only that of life insurance and shall not be applied directly or indirectly ^17*** for any`
  line `purposes ^18[other than those of the life insurance business of the insurer].`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1968, s. 8, for "classes specified in clause (a), (b), (c) and (d) of sub-section (1) of section 7"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (1) Added by Act 13 of 1941, s. 8 (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 62 of 1968, s. 8, for "the class specified in clause (d) of that sub-section" (w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 41of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 62 of 1968, s. 8, for "each such sub-class of the class specified in clause (d)" (w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 15, for "prescribed in this behalf" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 62 of 1968, s. 8, for "the class of insurance business specified in clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 7" (w.e.f.`
  line `1-6-1969).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 13 of 1941, s. 8, for "the excess of receipts over payments in respect of such business" (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 6 of 1946, s. 8 (w.e.f. 20-3-1946).`
  line
  line `10. The words, brackets and figures, "after the expiry of six months from the commencement of the Insurance (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1946 (6 of 1946)" omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 15 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 6 of 1946, s. 8, for "part of such fund" (w.e.f. 20-3-1946).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 47 of 1950, s. 11, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
  line
  line `13. The words "under the law of the insure's country" omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 15 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 41of 1999, s. 30 and The First Schedule, for “Controller” (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `15. Ins. by Act 6 of 1946, s. 8 (w.e.f. 20-3-1946).`
  line
  line `16. Ins. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 15 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `17. The words "save as provided in section 49" omitted by Act 13 of 1941, s. 8 (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "other than those of life insurance" (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (18118)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 24
  title `Accounts and balance-sheet.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 16, for section 11 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18118&sectionno=11&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Accounts and balance-sheet. --(1) Every insurer, on or after the date of the commencement of`
  line `the Insurance Laws (Amendment) Act, 2015 (5 of 2015), in respect of insurance business transacted by`
  line `him and in respect of his shareholders' funds, shall, at the expiration of each financial year, prepare with`
  line `reference to that year, balance sheet, a profit and loss account, a separate account of receipts and`
  line `payments, a revenue account in accordance with the regulations as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) Every insurer shall keep separate accounts relating to funds of shareholders and policyholders.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless the insurer is a company as defined in clause (20) of section 2 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), the accounts and statements referred to in sub-section (1) shall be signed by the`
  line `insurer, or in the case of a company by the chairman, if any, and two directors and the principal officer of`
  line `the company, or in case of an insurance cooperative society by the person in charge of the society and`
  line `shall be accompanied by a statement containing the names, descriptions and occupations of, and the`
  line `directorships held by, the persons in charge of the management of the business during the period to which`
  line `such accounts and statements refer and by a report on the affairs of the business during that period.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (18119)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 25
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 17, for section 12 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18119&sectionno=12&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Audit.-- The balance sheet, profit and loss account, revenue account and profit and loss`
  line `appropriation account of every insurer, in respect of all insurance business transacted by him, shall, unless`
  line `they are subject to audit under the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), be audited annually by an auditor,`
  line `and the auditor shall in the audit of all such accounts have the powers of, exercise the functions vested in,`
  line `and discharge the duties and be subject to the liabilities and penalties imposed on, auditors of companies`
  line `by section 147 of the Companies Act, 2013.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (18120)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 26
  title `Actuarial report and abstract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18120&sectionno=13&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every insurer carrying on life insurance business shall,`
  line `once at least every year cause an investigation to be made by an actuary into the financial condition of the`
  line `life insurance business carried on by him, including a valuation of his liabilities in respect thereto and`
  line `shall cause an abstract of the report of such actuary to be made in accordance with the regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority may, having regard to the circumstances of any particular insurer, allow`
  line `him to have the investigation made as at a date not later than two years from the date as at which the`
  line `previous investigation was made:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every insurer, on or after the commencement of the Insurance Regulatory and`
  line `Development Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999), shall cause an abstract of the report of the actuary to be`
  line `made in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.]`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) regarding the making of an abstract shall apply whenever at any`
  line `other time an investigation into the financial condition of the insurer is made with a view to the`
  line `distribution of profits or an investigation is made of which the results are made public.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be appended to every such abstract as is referred to in sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) a certificate signed by the principal officer of the insurer that full and accurate particulars`
  line `of every policy under which there is a liability either actual or contingent have been furnished to the`
  line `actuary for the purpose of the investigation.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) There shall be appended to every such abstract a statement prepared in such form and in such`
  line `manner as may be specified by the regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the investigation referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) is made annually by any`
  line `insurer, the statement need not be appended every year but shall be appended at least once in every three`
  line years.]
  line
  line `(5) Where an investigation into the financial condition of an insurer is made as at a date other than the`
  line `expiration of the year of account, the accounts for the period since the expiration of the last year of`
  line `account and the balance-sheet as at the date at which the investigation is made shall be prepared and`
  line `audited in the manner provided by this Act.`
  line
  line `^3[(6) The provisions of this section relating to the life insurance business shall apply also to any such`
  line `sub-class of insurance business included in the class "Miscellaneous Insurance" and the Authority may`
  line `authorise such modifications and variations of regulations as may be necessary to facilitate their`
  line `application to any such sub-class of insurance business:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the Authority is satisfied that the number and amount of the transactions carried out`
  line `by an insurer in any such sub-class of insurance business is so small as to render periodic investigation`
  line `and valuation unnecessary, it may exempt that insurer from the operation of this sub-section in respect of`
  line `that sub-class of insurance business.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014)`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (18121)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 27
  title `Record of policies and claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 19 for section 14 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18121&sectionno=14&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Record of policies and claims.--(1) Every insurer, in respect of all business transacted by him,`
  line `shall maintain--`
  line
  line `(a) a record of policies, in which shall be entered, in respect of every policy issued by the insurer,`
  line `the name and address of the policyholder, the date when the policy was effected and a record of any`
  line `transfer, assignment or nomination of which the insurer has notice;`
  line
  line `(b) a record of claims, every claim made together with the date of the claim, the name and address`
  line `of the claimant and the date on which the claim was discharged, or, in the case of a claim which is`
  line `rejected, the date of rejection and the grounds thereof; and`
  line
  line `(c) a record of policies and claims in accordance with clauses (a) and (b) may be maintained in`
  line `any such form, including electronic mode, as may be specified by the regulations made under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) Every insurer shall, in respect of all business transacted by him, endeavour to issue policies above`
  line `a specified threshold in terms of sum assured and premium in electronic form, in the manner and form to`
  line `be specified by the regulations made under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (18122)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 28
  title `Submission of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for section 15 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18122&sectionno=15&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Submission of returns.--(1) The audited accounts and statements referred to in section 11 or`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 13 and the abstract and statement referred to in section 13 shall be printed, and`
  line `four copies thereof shall be furnished as returns to the Authority within six months from the end of the`
  line `period to which they refer.`
  line
  line `(2) Of the four copies so furnished, one shall be signed in the case of a company by the chairman and`
  line `two directors and by the principal officer of the company and, if the company has a managing director by`
  line `that managing director and one shall be signed by the auditor who made the audit or the actuary who`
  line `made the valuation, as the case may be.]`
