obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (18126)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 32
  title `Furnishing reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and The First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18126&sectionno=18&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every insurer shall furnish to the ^1[Authority] a certified copy of every`
  line `report on the affairs of the concern which is submitted to the members or policy-holders of the insurer`
  line `immediately after its submission to the members or policy-holders, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (18127)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 33
  title `Abstract of proceedings of general meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18127&sectionno=19&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Every insurer, being a company or body`
  line `incorporated under any law for the time being in force in ^2[India], shall furnish to the ^1[Authority]`
  line `^3[a certified copy of the minutes of the proceedings of every general meeting, as entered in the`
  line `Minutes Book of the insurer] within thirty days from the holding of the meeting to which it relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and The First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Subs by Act 47 of 1950, s. 14, for "an abstract of the proceedings of every general meeting" (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (18128)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 34
  title `Custody and inspection of documents and supply of copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18128&sectionno=20&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every return furnished to`
  line `the Authority or certified copy thereof shall be kept by the Authority and shall be open to inspection; and`
  line `any person may procure a copy of any such return, or of any part thereof, on payment of such fee as may`
  line `be specified by the regulations.]`
  line
  line `(2) A printed or certified copy of the accounts, statements and abstract furnished in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of section 15 ^2*** shall, on the application of any shareholder or policy-holder made at any`
  line `time within two years from the date on which the documents was so furnished, be supplied to him by the`
  line `insurer within fourteen days when the insurer is constituted, incorporated or domiciled in ^3[India] and in`
  line `any other case within one month of such application.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the memorandum and articles of association of the insurer, if a company shall on the`
  line `application of any policy-holder, be supplied to him by the insurer on payment of ^4[such fee as may be`
  line `specified by the regulations].`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 23, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by 5 of 2015, s. 23, for "one rupee" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (18129)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers of Authority regarding returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18129&sectionno=21&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `21. Powers of ^2[Authority] regarding returns. -- (1) If it appears to the ^5[Authority] that any return`
  line `furnished to him under the provisions of this Act is inaccurate or defective in any respect, he`
  line may--
  line
  line `(a) require from the insurer such further information, certified if he so directs by an auditor or`
  line `actuary, as he may consider necessary to correct or supplement such return;`
  line
  line `(b) call upon the insurer to submit for his examination at the principal place of business of the`
  line `insurer in ^1[India] any book of account, register or other document or to supply any statement`
  line `which his may specify in a notice served on the insurer for the purpose;`
  line
  line `(c) examine any office of the insurer on oath in relation to the return;`
  line
  line `(d) decline to accept any such return unless the inaccuracy has been corrected or the`
  line `deficiency has been supplied before the expiry of one month from the date on which the requisition`
  line `asking for correction of (he inaccuracy or supply of the deficiency was delivered to the insurer ^3[or of`
  line `such further time as the ^2[Authority] may specify in the requisition] and if him declines to accept any`
  line `such return, the insurer shall be deemed to have failed to comply with the provisions of`
  line `section 15 ^4*** ^5[or section 28] ^6[or section 28A ^7 or section 28B or section 64V] relating to the`
  line `furnishing of returns.`
  line
  line `^8[(2) The Securities Appellate Tribunal may, on the application of an insurer and after hearing the`
  line `Authority, cancel any order made by the Authority under clause (d) of sub-section (1) or may direct the`
  line `acceptance of such a return which the Authority has declined to accept, if the insurer satisfies the Tribunal`
  line `that the action of the Authority was in the circumstances unreasonable:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application under this sub-section shall be entertained unless it is made before the`
  line `expiration of four months from the date when the Authority made the order or declined to accept the`
  line return.]
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 47 of 1950, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
  line
  line `4. The words and figures "or section 16" omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 24 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 6 of 1946, s. 13 (w.e.f. 20-3-1946).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 47of 1950, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 6 of 1968, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 24 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (18130)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 36
  title `Powers of Authority to order revaluation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18130&sectionno=22&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `22. Power of ^1[Authority] to order revaluation.-- ^2[(1)] If it appears to the ^1[Authority] that an`
  line `investigation or valuation to which section 13 refers ^3*** does not properly indicate the condition of the`
  line `affairs of the insurer by reason of the faulty basis adopted in the valuation, he may, after giving notice to`
  line `the insurer and giving him an opportunity to be heard, cause an investigation and valuation ^4[as at such`
  line `date as the ^1[Authority] may specify] to be made at the expense of the insurer by an actuary appointed by`
  line `the insurer for this purpose and approved by the ^1[Authority] and ^4[and the insurer shall place at the`
  line `disposal of the actuary so appointed and approved all the material required by the actuary for the purposes`
  line `of the investigation and valuation within such period, not being less than three months, as the ^1[Authority]`
  line `may specify],`
  line
  line `^5[(2) The provisions of sub-sections (1) and (4) of section 13, and of sub-sections (I) and (2) of`
  line `section ^6***, shall apply in relation to an investigation and valuation under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that the abstract and statement prepared as the result of such investigation and valuation`
  line `shall be furnished by such date as the ^1[Authority] may specify.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Section 22 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 6 of 1946, s. 14 (w.e.f. 20-3-1946).`
  line
  line `3. The words, brackets, letter and figures "or an abstract of a valuation report furnished under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 16" omitted by Act 5 of 2015 s. 25 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 6 of 1946, s. 14 (w.e.f. 20-3-1946).`
  line
  line `5. Added by s. 14, ibid., (w.e.f. 20-3-1946).`
  line
  line `6. The words, brackets, letter and figures "or, as the case may be, of sub-section (2) of section 16" omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 25`
  line `(w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (18131)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 37
  title `Evidence of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18131&sectionno=23&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every return furnished to the ^1[Authority] which has been`
  line `certified by the ^1[Authority] to be a return so furnished, shall be deemed to be a return so furnished.`
  line
  line `(2) Every document, purporting to be certified by the ^1[Authority] to be a copy of a return so`
  line `furnished, shall be deemed to be a copy of that return and shall be received in evidence as if it were the`
  line `original return, unless some variation between it and the original return is proved.`
