obj_root_law_sections_34_h:
  sectionId (18162)
  sectionNo 34H
  orderNo 68
  title `Search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18162&sectionno=34H&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_34_h_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the ^1[Chairperson of the Authority], in consequence of`
  line `information in his possession, has reason to believe that --`
  line
  line `(a) any person who has been required under sub-section (2) of section 33 to produce, or cause to`
  line `be produced, any books, accounts or other documents in his custody or power has omitted or failed to`
  line `produce, or cause to be produced, such books, accounts or other documents, or`
  line
  line `(b) Any person to whom a requisition to produce any books, accounts or other documents as`
  line `aforesaid has been or might be issued will not, or would not, produce or cause to be produced, any`
  line `books, accounts or other documents which will be useful for, or relevant to, an investigation under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 33 or an inspection under sub-section (1A) of that section, or`
  line
  line `(c) a contravention of any provision of this Act has been committed or is likely to be committed`
  line `by an insurer, or`
  line
  line `(d) any claim which is due to be settled by an insurer, has been or is likely to be rejected or`
  line `settled at a figure higher than a reasonable amount, or`
  line
  line `(e) any claim which is due to be settled by an insurer, has been or is likely to be rejected or settled`
  line `at a figure lower than a reasonable amount, or`
  line
  line `(f) any illegal rebate or commission has been paid or is likely to be paid by an insurer, or`
  line
  line `(g) any books, accounts, receipts, vouchers, survey reports or other documents, belonging to an`
  line `insurer are likely to be tampered with, falsified or manufactured,`
  line
  line `he may authorise any subordinate officer of his, not lower in rank than ^2[a Deputy Director or an`
  line `equivalent officer] (hereafter referred to as the authorised officer) to --`
  line
  line `(i) enter and search any building or place where he has reason to suspect that such books, accounts`
  line `or other documents, or any books or papers relating to any claim, rebate or commission or any`
  line `receipts, vouchers, reports or other documents are kept;`
  line
  line `(ii) break open the lock of any door, box, locker, safe, almirah or other receptacle for exercising`
  line `the powers conferred by clause (i) where the keys thereof are not available;`
  line
  line `(iii) seize all or any such books, accounts or other documents, found as a result of such search;`
  line
  line `(iv) place marks of identification on such books, accounts or other documents or make or cause to`
  line `be made extracts or copies therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) The authorised officer may requisition the services of any police-officer or of any officer of the`
  line `Central Government, or of both, to assist hi m for all or any of the purposes specified in sub-section (1)`
  line `and it shall be the duty of every such officer to comply with such requisition.`
  line
  line `(3) The authorised officer may, where it is not practicable to seize any such book, account or other`
  line `document, specified in sub-section (1), serve an order on the person who is in immediate possession or`
  line `control thereof that he shall not remove, part with or otherwise deal with it except with the previous`
  line `permission of such officer and such officer may take such steps as may be necessary for ensuring`
  line `compliance with this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The authorised officer may, during the course of the search or seizure, examine on oath any`
  line `person who is found to be in possession or control of any books, accounts or other documents, and any`
  line `statement made by such person during such examination may thereafter be used in evidence in any`
  line `proceeding under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The books, accounts, papers, receipts, vouchers, reports, or other documents seized under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall not be retained by the authorised officer for a period exceeding one hundred and`
  line `eighty days from the date of the seizure unless the reasons for retaining the same recorded by hi m in`
  line `writing and the approval of the ^3[Chairperson of the Authority] for such retention is obtained:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^3[Chairperson of the Authority] shall not authorise the retention of the books,`
  line `accounts, papers, receipts, vouchers, reports, or other documents for a period exceeding thirty days after`
  line `all the proceedings under this Act for which the books, accounts, papers, receipts, vouchers, reports, or`
  line `other documents are relevant are completed.`
  line
  line `(6 ) The person from whose custody and books, accounts, papers, receipts, vouchers, reports, or other`
  line `documents are seized under sub-section (1) may make copies thereof, or take extracts therefrom, in the`
  line `presence of the authorised officer or any other person empowered by hi m in this behalf at such place and`
  line `time as the authorised officer may appoint in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(7) If a person legally entitled to the books, accounts, papers, receipts, vouchers, reports or other`
  line `documents seized under sub-section (1) objects for any reason to the approval given by the`
  line `^4[Chairperson of the Authority] under sub-section (5), he may make an application to the ^5[Securities`
  line `Appellate Tribunal] stating therein the reason for such objection and requesting for the return of the`
  line `books, accounts, papers, receipts, vouchers, reports or other documents.`
  line
  line `(8) On receipt of the application under sub-section (7), the ^5[Securities Appellate Tribunal] may, after`
  line `giving the applicant an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(9) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898) relating to searches and`
  line `seizures shall apply, so far as may be, to every search and seizure made under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(10) The Central Government ^6[ may, by notification in the Official Gazette; make rules] in relation to`
  line `any search or seizure under this section; in particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the`
  line `foregoing power, such rules may provide for the procedure to be followed by the authorised officer, --`
  line
  line `(i) for obtaining ingress into such building or place to be searched where free ingress thereto is`
  line `not available;`
  line
  line `(ii) for ensuring safe custody of any books, accounts, papers, receipts, vouchers, reports, or other`
  line `documents seized under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_h_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 30 and the First Schedule, [Serial no. 22 (a)], ibid., for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 41, for "an officer authorised by the Authority" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 62 of 1968, s. 33 and the First Schedule [Serial no. 22 (b)], for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule for [Serial no. 22 (b)] "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 41, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "may make rules" (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (18163)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 69
  title `Amalgamation and transfer of insurance business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18163&sectionno=35&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in any other law for the time being in force, no insurance business of an insurer shall be transferred to or`
  line `amalgamated with the insurance business of any other insurer except in accordance with a scheme`
  line `prepared under this section and approved by the Authority.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any scheme prepared under this section shall set out the agreement under which the transfer or`
  line `amalgamation is proposed to be effected, and shall contain such further provisions as may be necessary`
  line `for giving effect to the scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) Before an application is made to the ^2[Authority] ^3[to approve any such scheme] notices of the`
  line `intention to make the application together with a statement of the nature of the amalgamation or transfer,`
  line `as the case may be, and of the reason therefore shall, at least two months before the application is made,`
  line `be sent to the ^2[Authority] ^4[and certified copies, four in number, of each of the following documents shall`
  line `be furnished to the ^2[Authority], and other such copies shall] during the two months aforesaid be kept`
  line `open for the inspection of the members and policy-holders at the principal and branch offices and chief`
  line `agencies of the insurers concerned, namely: --`
  line
  line `(a) a draft of the agreement or deed under which it is proposed to effect the amalgamation or`
  line transfer;
  line
  line `^5[(b) balance sheets in respect of the insurance business of each of the insurers concerned in such`
  line `amalgamation or transfer, prepared in such forms as may be specified by the regulations;`
  line
  line `(c) actuarial reports and abstracts in respect of the life insurance business of each of the insurers`
  line `so concerned, prepared in conformity with the regulations specified in this regard.]`
  line
  line `(d) a report on the proposed amalgamation or transfer, prepared by an independent actuary who`
  line `has never been professionally connected with any of the parties concerned in the amalgamation or`
  line `transfer at any time in the five years preceding the date on which he signs hi s report;`
  line
  line `(e) any other reports on which the scheme of amalgamation or transfer was founded.`
  line
  line `The balance-sheets, reports and abstracts referred to in clauses (b), (c) and (d) shall be prepared as at the`
  line `date at which ^6[the amalgamation or transfer if approved] by the ^7[Authority] is to take effect, which date`
  line `shall not be more than twelve months before the date on which the application to the ^7[Authority] is made`
  line `under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the ^7[Authority] so directs in the case of any particular insurer there may be`
  line `substituted respectively for the balance-sheet, report and abstract referred to in clauses (b) and (c)`
  line `prepared in accordance with this sub-section certified copies of the last balance-sheet and last report and`
  line `abstract prepared in accordance with sections 11 and 13 ^8[of this Act or sections 7 and 8 of the Indian`
  line `Life Assurance Companies Act, 1912 ( 6 of 1912 ),] if that balance-sheet is prepared as at a date not more`
  line `than twelve months, and that report and abstract as at a date not more than five years, before the date on`
  line `which the application to the ^7[Authority] is made under this section].`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 42, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 30 and the First Schedule, ibid., for "to sanction any such scheme" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 1941, s. 22, for "and certified copies of the following documents shall be furnished to the Central`
  line `Government and shall" (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 42, for clauses (b) and (c) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "the amalgamation or transfer if sanctioned" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 30 and the First Schedule, ibid., for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000). Earlier subs. by Act 47 of 1950, s. 26, for`
  line `"Court" (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 13 of 1941, s. 22 (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (18164)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 70
  title `Sanction of amalgamation and transfer by Controller.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 43, for section 36 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18164&sectionno=36&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1[36. Sanction of amalgamation and transfer by Authority.--When any application under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 35 is made to the Authority, the Authority shall cause, a notice of the`
  line `application to be given to the holders of any kind of policy of insurer concerned alongwith statement of`
  line `the nature and terms of the amalgamation or transfer, as the case may be, to be published in such manner`
  line `and for such period as it may direct, and, after hearing the directors and considering the objections of the`
  line `policyholders and any other persons whom it considers entitled to be heard, may approve the`
  line `arrangement, and shall make such consequential orders as are necessary to give effect to the`
  line arrangement.]
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (18165)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 71
  title `Statements required after amalgamation and transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18165&sectionno=37&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Where an amalgamation takes place`
  line `between any two or more insurers, or ^2[where any business of an insurer is transferred], whether in`
  line `accordance with a scheme confirmed by the ^1[Authority] or otherwise, the insurer carrying on the`
  line `amalgamated business or ^3[the person to whom the business is transferred], as the case may be, shall,`
  line `within three months from the date of the completion of the amalgamation or transfer, ^4[furnish in`
  line `duplicate to the ^1[Authority]] --`
  line
  line `(a) a certified copy of the scheme, agreement or deed under which the amalgamation or transfer has`
  line `been effected, and`
  line
  line `(b) ^5[ a declaration signed by every party concerned] or in the case of a company by the chairman and`
  line `the principal officer that to the best of their belief every payment made or to be made to any person`
  line `whatsoever on account of the amalgamation or transfer is therein fully set forth and that no other`
  line `payments beyond those set forth have been made or are to be made either in money, policies, bonds,`
  line `valuable securities or other property by or with the knowledge of any parties to the amalgamation or`
  line `transfer, and`
  line
  line `^6[(c) where the amalgamation or transfer has not been made in accordance with a ^7[scheme approved]`
  line `by the ^8[Authority] under section 36--`
  line
  line `(i) balance-sheets in respect of the insurance business of each of the insurers concerned in such`
  line `amalgamation or transfer, prepared in the Form set forth in Part II of the First Schedule and in`
  line `accordance with the regulations contained in Part I of that Schedule, and`
  line
  line `(ii) certified copies of any other reports on which the scheme of amalgamation or transfer was`
  line founded.]
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 30 and the First Schedule, ibid., for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000). Earlier subs. by Act 47 of 1950, s. 26, for`
  line `"Court" (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1941, s. 24, for "where any business of one insurer is transferred to another" (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for "the insurer to whom the business is transferred" (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for "furnish to the Central Government" (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 13 of 1941, s. 21, for "a declaration signed by every insurer concerned" (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line `6. Subs. s. 24, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 the First Schedule, for "scheme sanctioned" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 30, and the First Schedule, ibid., for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_37_a:
  sectionId (18166)
  sectionNo 37A
  orderNo 72
  title `Power of Authority to prepare Scheme of Amalgamation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18166&sectionno=37A&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content:
  string
  line `^2[37A. Power of ^1[Authority] to prepare Scheme of Amalgamation. --(1) If the ^1[Authority] is`
  line `satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(i) in the public interest; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in the interests of the policy-holders; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in order to secure the proper management of an insurer; or`
  line
  line `(iv) in the interest of insurance business of the country as a whole,`
  line
  line `it is necessary so to do, he may prepare a scheme for the amalgamation of that insurer with any other`
  line `insurer (hereinafter referred to in this section as the transferee insurer):`
  line
  line `Provided that no such scheme shall be prepared unless the other insurer has given his written consent`
  line `to the proposal for such amalgamation.`
  line
  line `(2) The scheme aforesaid may contain provisions for all or any of the following matters, namely: --`
  line
  line `(a) the constitution, name and registered office, the capital, assets, powers, rights, interests,`
  line `authorities and privileges, and the liabilities, duties and obligations of the transferee insurer;`
  line
  line `(b) the transfer to the transferee insurer of the business, properties, assets and liabilities of the`
  line `insurer on such terms and conditions as may be specified in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) any change in the Board of Directors, or the appointment of a new Board of Directors of the`
  line `transferee insurer and the authority by whom, the manner in which, and the other terms and`
  line `conditions on which, such change or appointment shall be made, and, in the case of appointment of a`
  line `new Board of Directors or of any director, the period for which such appointment shall be made;`
  line
  line `(d) the alteration of the memorandum and articles of association of the transferee insurer for the`
  line `purpose of altering the capital thereof or for such other purposes as may be necessary to give effect to`
  line `the amalgamation;`
  line
  line `(e) subject to the provisions of the scheme, the continuation by or against the transferee insurer,`
  line `of any actions or proceedings pending against the insurer;`
  line
  line `(f) the reduction of the interest or rights which the shareholders, policy-holders and other`
  line `creditors have in or against the insurer before the amalgamation to such extent as the`
  line 2[Authority[
  line `considers necessary in the public interest or in the interests of the shareholders, policy-holders and`
  line `other creditors or for the maintenance of the business of the insurer;`
  line
  line `(g) the payment in cash or otherwise to policy-holders, and other creditors in full satisfaction of`
  line `their claim,--`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of their interest or rights in or against the insurer before the amalgamation; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where their interest or rights aforesaid in or against the insurer has or have been reduced`
  line `under clause (f) in respect of such interest or rights as so reduced;`
  line
  line `(h) the allotment to the shareholders of the insurer for shares held by them therein before the`
  line `amalgamation whether their interest in such shares has been reduced under clause (f) or not of shares`
  line `in the transferee insurer and where any shareholders claim payment in cash and not allotment of`
  line `shares, or where it is not possible to allot shares to any shareholders, the payment in cash to those`
  line `shareholders in full satisfaction of their claim--`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of their interest in shares in the insurer before the amalgamation; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where such interest has been reduced under clause (f) in respect of their interest in shares`
  line `as so reduced;`
  line
  line `(i) the continuance of the services of all the employees of the insurer (excepting such of them as`
  line `not being workmen within the meaning of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), are`
  line `specifically mentioned in the scheme) in the transferee insurer at the same remuneration and on the`
  line `same terms and conditions of service, which they were getting or, as the case may be, by which they`
  line `were being governed, immediately before the date of the amalgamation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the scheme shall contain a provision that the transferee insurer shall pay or grant`
  line `not later than the expiry of the period of three years, from the date of the amalgamation, to the said`
  line `employees the same remuneration and the same terms and conditions of service as are applicable to`
  line `the other employees of corresponding rank or status, of the transferee insurer subject to the`
  line `qualifications and experience of the said employees being the same as or equivalent to those of such`
  line `other employees of the transferee insurer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if in any case any doubt or difference arises as to whether the qualification`
  line `and experience of any of the said employees are the same as or equivalent to the qualifications and`
  line `experience of the other employees of corresponding rank or status of the transferee insurer, the doubt`
  line `or difference shall be referred to the Controller whose decision thereon shall be final;`
  line
  line `(j) notwithstanding anything contained in clause (i) where any of the employees of the insurer not`
  line `being workmen within the meaning of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), are`
  line `specifically mentioned in the scheme under clause (i) of where any employees of the insurer have by`
  line `notice in writing given to the insurer or, as the case may be, the transferee insurer at any time before`
  line `the expiry of one month next following the date on which the scheme is sanctioned by the Central`
  line `Government, intimated their intention of not becoming employees of the transferee insurer, the payment to such employees of compensation, if any, to which they are entitled under the Industrial`
  line `Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), and such pension, gratuity, provident fund, or other retirement`
  line `benefits ordinarily admissible to them under the rules or authorisations of the insurer immediately`
  line `before the date of the amalgamation;`
  line
  line `(k) any other terms and conditions for the amalgamation of the insurer;`
  line
  line `(l) such incidental, consequential and supplemental matters as are necessary to secure that the`
  line `amalgamation shall be fully and effectively carried out.`
  line
  line `(3)(a) A copy of the scheme prepared by the ^3[Authority] shall be sent in draft to the insurer and also`
  line `to the transferee insurer and any other insurer concerned in the amalgamation, for suggestions and`
  line `objections, if any, within such period as the ^3Authority] may specify for this purpose.`
  line
  line `(b) The ^3[Authority] may make such modifications, if any, in the draft scheme as he may consider`
  line `necessary in the light of the suggestions and objections received from the insurer and also from the`
  line `transferee insurer and any other insurer concerned in the amalgamation and from any shareholder, policyholder`
  line `or other creditor of each of those insurers and the transferee insurer.`
  line
  line `^4[(4) The scheme shall thereafter be placed before the Central Government for its sanction and the`
  line `Central Government may sanction the scheme without any modification or with such modifications as it`
  line `may consider necessary, and the scheme as sanctioned by the Central Government shall come into force`
  line `on such date as the Central Government may notify in this behalf in the Official Gazette:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be specified for different provisions of the scheme.`
  line
  line `(4A) Every policyholder or shareholder or member of each of the insurers, before amalgamation, shall`
  line `have the same interest in, or rights against the insurer resulting from amalgamation as he had in the`
  line `company of which he was originally a policyholder or shareholder or member:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the interests or rights of any shareholder or member are less than his interest in,`
  line `or rights against, the original insurer, he shall be entitled to compensation, which shall be assessed by the`
  line `Authority in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(4B) The compensation so assessed shall be paid to the shareholder or member by the insurance`
  line `company resulting from such amalgamation.`
  line
  line `(4C) Any member or shareholder aggrieved by the assessment of compensation made by the`
  line `Authority under sub-section (4A) may within thirty days from the publication of such assessment prefer`
  line `an appeal to the Securities Appellate Tribunal.]`
  line
  line `(5) The sanction accorded by the Central Government under sub-section (4) shall be conclusive`
  line `evidence that all the requirements of this section relating to amalgamation have been complied with and a`
  line `copy of the sanctioned scheme certified in writing by an officer of the Central Government to be a true`
  line `copy thereof shall, in all legal proceedings (whether in appeal or otherwise) be admitted as evidence to`
  line `the same extent as the original scheme.`
  line
  line `(6) The ^3[Authority] may, in like manner, add to amend or vary any scheme made under this section.`
  line
  line `(7) On and from the date of the coming into operation of the scheme or any provision thereof, the`
  line `scheme or such provision shall be binding on the insurer or, as the case may be, on the transferee insurer`
  line `and any other insurer concerned in the amalgamation and also on all the shareholders, policy-holders and other creditors and employees of each of those insurers and of transferee insurer, and on any other person`
  line `having any right or liability in relation to any of those insurers or the transferee insurer.`
  line
  line `(8) On and from such date as may be specified by the Central Government in this behalf, the`
  line `properties and assets of the insurer shall, by virtue of and to the extent provided in the scheme, stand`
  line `transferred to, and vest in, and the liabilities of the insurer shall, by virtue of and to the extent provided in`
  line `the scheme, stand transferred to and become the liabilities of the transferee insurer.`
  line
  line `(9) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of the scheme, the Central Government`
  line `may by order do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to it necessary or`
  line `expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
  line
  line `(10) Copies of every scheme made under this section and of every order made under sub-section (9)`
  line `shall be laid before each House of Parliament, as soon as may be, after the scheme has been sanctioned by`
  line `the Central Government, or as the case may be, the order has been made.`
  line
  line `(11) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent the amalgamation with an insurer by a single`
  line `scheme of several insurers.`
  line
  line `(12) The provisions of this section and of any scheme made under it shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in any other provisions of this Act or in any other law or any`
  line `agreement, award or other instrument for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(13) The provisions of section 37 shall not apply to an amalgamation given effect to under the`
  line `provisions of this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 30, and the First Schedule, ibid., for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 62 of 1968, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s 44, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (18167)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 73
  title `Assignment and transfer of insurance policies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 45, for sections 38, 39 and 40 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18167&sectionno=38&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1[38. Assignment and transfer of insurance policies. --(1) A transfer or assignment of a policy of`
  line `insurance, wholly or in part, whether with or without consideration, may be made only by an endorsement`
  line `upon the policy itself or by a separate instrument, signed in either case by the transferor or by the assignor`
  line `or his duly authorised agent and attested by at least one witness, specifically setting forth the fact of`
  line `transfer or assignment and the reasons thereof, the antecedents of the assignee and the terms on which the`
  line `assignment is made.`
  line
  line `(2) An insurer may, accept the transfer or assignment, or decline to act upon any endorsement made`
  line `under sub-section (1), where it has sufficient reason to believe that such transfer or assignment is not`
  line `bona fide or is not in the interest of the policyholder or in public interest or is for the purpose of trading of`
  line `insurance policy.`
  line
  line `(3) The insurer shall, before refusing to act upon the endorsement, record in writing the reasons for`
  line `such refusal and communicate the same to the policyholder not later than thirty days from the date of the`
  line `policyholder giving notice of such transfer or assignment.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by the decision of an insurer to decline to act upon such transfer or`
  line `assignment may within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt of the communication from the`
  line `insurer containing reasons for such refusal, prefer a claim to the Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions in sub-section (2), the transfer or assignment shall be complete and`
  line `effectual upon the execution of such endorsement or instrument duly attested but except, where the`
  line `transfer or assignment is in favour of the insurer, shall not be operative as against an insurer, and shall not`
  line `confer upon the transferee or assignee, or his legal representative, any right to sue for the amount of such`
  line `policy or the moneys secured thereby until a notice in writing of the transfer or assignment and either the`
  line
  line `said endorsement or instrument itself or a copy thereof certified to be correct by both transferor and`
  line `transferee or their duly authorised agents have been delivered to the insurer:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the insurer maintains one or more places of business in India, such notice shall`
  line `be delivered only at the place where the policy is being serviced.`
  line
  line `(6) The date on which the notice referred to in sub-section (5) is delivered to the insurer shall regulate`
  line `the priority of all claims under a transfer or assignment as between persons interested in the policy; and`
  line `where there is more than one instrument of transfer or assignment the priority of the claims under such`
  line `instruments shall be governed by the order in which the notices referred to in sub-section (5) are`
  line `delivered:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any dispute as to priority of payment arises as between assignees, the dispute shall be`
  line `referred to the Authority.`
  line
  line `(7) Upon the receipt of the notice referred to in sub-section (5), the insurer shall record the fact of`
  line `such transfer or assignment together with the date thereof and the name of the transferee or the assignee`
  line `and shall, on the request of the person by whom the notice was given, or of the transferee or assignee, on`
  line `payment of such fee as may be specified by the regulations, grant a written acknowledgement of the`
  line `receipt of such notice; and any such acknowledgement shall be conclusive evidence against the insurer`
  line `that he has duly received the notice to which such acknowledgement relates.`
  line
  line `(8) Subject to the terms and conditions of the transfer or assignment, the insurer shall, from the date`
  line `of the receipt of the notice referred to in sub-section (5), recognise the transferee or assignee named in the`
  line `notice as the absolute transferee or assignee entitled to benefit under the policy, and such person shall be`
  line `subject to all liabilities and equities to which the transferor or assignor was subject at the date of the`
  line `transfer or assignment and may institute any proceedings in relation to the policy, obtain a loan under the`
  line `policy or surrender the policy without obtaining the consent of the transferor or assignor or making him a`
  line `party to such proceedings.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- Except where the endorsement referred to in sub-section (1) expressly indicates that`
  line `the assignment or transfer is conditional in terms of sub-section (10) hereunder, every assignment or`
  line `transfer shall be deemed to be an absolute assignment or transfer and the assignee or transferee, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be deemed to be the absolute assignee or transferee respectively.`
  line
  line `(9) Any rights and remedies of an assignee or transferee of a policy of life insurance under an`
  line `assignment or transfer effected prior to the commencement of the Insurance Laws (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2015 (5 of 2015) shall not be affected by the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(10) Notwithstanding any law or custom having the force of law to the contrary, an assignment in`
  line `favour of a person made upon the condition that--`
  line
  line `(a) the proceeds under the policy shall become payable to the policyholder or the nominee or`
  line `nominees in the event of either the assignee or transferee predeceasing the insured; or`
  line
  line `(b) the insured surviving the term of the policy, shall be valid:`
  line
  line `Provided that a conditional assignee shall not be entitled to obtain a loan on the policy or surrender a`
  line policy.
  line
  line `(11) In the case of the partial assignment or transfer of a policy of insurance under sub-section (1), the`
  line `liability of the insurer shall be limited to the amount secured by partial assignment or transfer and such policyholder shall not be entitled to further assign or transfer the residual amount payable under the same`
  line policy.]
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (18168)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 74
  title `Nomination by policy-holder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 45, for sections 38, 39 and 40 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18168&sectionno=39&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1[39. Nomination by policyholder. --(1) The holder of a policy of life insurance on his own life may,`
  line `when effecting the policy or at any time before the policy matures for payment, nominate the person or`
  line `persons to whom the money secured by the policy shall be paid in the event of his death:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where any nominee is a minor, it shall be lawful for the policyholder to appoint any`
  line `person in the manner laid down by the insurer, to receive the money secured by the policy in the event of`
  line `his death during the minority of the nominee.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such nomination in order to be effectual shall, unless it is incorporated in the text of the`
  line `policy itself, be made by an endorsement on the policy communicated to the insurer and registered by him`
  line `in the records relating to the policy and any such nomination may at any time before the policy matures`
  line `for payment be cancelled or changed by an endorsement or a further endorsement or a will, as the case`
  line `may be, but unless notice in writing of any such cancellation or change has been delivered to the insurer,`
  line `the insurer shall not be liable for any payment under the policy made bona fide by him to a nominee`
  line `mentioned in the text of the policy or registered in records of the insurer.`
  line
  line `(3) The insurer shall furnish to the policyholder a written acknowledgement of having registered a`
  line `nomination or a cancellation or change thereof, and may charge such fee as may be specified by`
  line `regulations for registering such cancellation or change.`
  line
  line `(4) A transfer or assignment of a policy made in accordance with section 38 shall automatically`
  line `cancel a nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that the assignment of a policy to the insurer who bears the risk on the policy at the time of`
  line `the assignment, in consideration of a loan granted by that insurer on the security of the policy within its`
  line `surrender value, or its reassignment on repayment of the loan shall not cancel a nomination, but shall`
  line `affect the rights of the nominee only to the extent of the insurer's interest in the policy:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the transfer or assignment of a policy, whether wholly or in part, in`
  line `consideration of a loan advanced by the transferee or assignee to the policyholder, shall not cancel the`
  line `nomination but shall affect the rights of the nominee only to the extent of the interest of the transferee or`
  line `assignee, as the case may be, in the policy:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the nomination, which has been automatically cancelled consequent upon the`
  line `transfer or assignment, the same nomination shall stand automatically revived when the policy is`
  line `reassigned by the assignee or retransferred by the transferee in favour of the policyholder on repayment of`
  line `loan other than on a security of policy to the insurer.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the policy matures for payment during the lifetime of the person whose life is insured or`
  line `where the nominee or, if there are more nominees than one, all the nominees die before the policy`
  line `matures for payment, the amount secured by the policy shall be payable to the policyholder or his heirs or`
  line `legal representatives or the holder of a succession certificate, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the nominee or if there are more nominees than one, a nominee or nominees survive the`
  line `person whose life is insured, the amount secured by the policy shall be payable to such survivor or`
  line survivors.
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the other provisions of this section, where the holder of a policy of insurance on his`
  line `own life nominates his parents, or his spouse, or his children, or his spouse and children, or any of them,`
  line `the nominee or nominees shall be beneficially entitled to the amount payable by the insurer to him or`
  line `them under sub-section (6) unless it is proved that the holder of the policy, having regard to the nature of`
  line `his title to the policy, could not have conferred any such beneficial title on the nominee.`
  line
  line `(8) Subject as aforesaid, where the nominee, or if there are more nominees than one, a nominee or`
  line `nominees, to whom sub-section (7) applies, die after the person whose life is insured but before the`
  line `amount secured by the policy is paid, the amount secured by the policy, or so much of the amount secured`
  line `by the policy as represents the share of the nominee or nominees so dying (as the case may be), shall be`
  line `payable to the heirs or legal representatives of the nominee or nominees or the holder of a succession`
  line `certificate, as the case may be, and they shall be beneficially entitled to such amount.`
  line
  line `(9) Nothing in sub-sections (7) and (8) shall operate to destroy or impede the right of any creditor to`
  line `be paid out of the proceeds of any policy of life insurance.`
  line
  line `(10) The provisions of sub-sections (7) and (8) shall apply to all policies of life insurance maturing`
  line `for payment after the commencement of the Insurance Laws (Amendment) Act, 2015 (5 of 2015).`
  line
  line `(11) Where a policyholder dies after the maturity of the policy but the proceeds and benefit of his`
  line `policy has not been made to him because of his death, in such a case, his nominee shall be entitled to the`
  line `proceeds and benefit of his policy.`
  line
  line `(12) The provisions of this section shall not apply to any policy of life insurance to which section 6 of`
  line `the Married Women's Property Act, 1874 (3 of 1874), applies or has at any time applied:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a nomination made whether before or after the commencement of the Insurance`
  line `Laws (Amendment) Act, 2015 (5 of 2015), in favour of the wife of the person who has insured his life or`
  line `of his wife and children or any of them is expressed, whether or not on the face of the policy, as being`
  line `made under this section, the said section 6 shall be deemed not to apply or not to have applied to the`
  line policy.]
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (18169)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 75
  title `Prohibition of payment by way of commission or otherwise for procuring business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 45, for sections 38, 39 and 40 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18169&sectionno=40&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `^1[40. Prohibition of payment by way of commission or otherwise for procuring business. --(1) No`
  line `person shall, pay or contract to pay any remuneration or reward, whether by way of commission or`
  line `otherwise for soliciting or procuring insurance business in India to any person except an insurance agent`
  line `or an intermediary or insurance intermediary in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) No insurance agent or intermediary or insurance intermediary shall receive or contract to receive`
  line `commission or remuneration in any form in respect of policies issued in India, by an insurer in any form`
  line `in respect of policies issued in India, by an insurer except in accordance with the regulations specified in`
  line `this regard:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority, while making regulations under sub-sections (1) and (2), shall take into`
  line `consideration the nature and tenure of the policy and in particular the interest of the agents and other`
  line `intermediaries concerned.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of section 102 in respect of a contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of the preceding sub-sections or the regulations framed in this regard, by an insurer, any`
  line `insurance agent or intermediary or insurance intermediary who contravenes the said provisions shall be`
  line `liable to a penalty which may extend to one lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_40_a:
  sectionId (18170)
  sectionNo 40A
  orderNo 76
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content
