  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18180&sectionno=44A&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_44_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[44A. Power to call for information.--For the purposes of ensuring compliance with the provisions`
  line `of sections 40, 40B and 40C, the Authority may, by notice--`
  line
  line `(a) require from an insurer such information, certified if so required by an auditor or actuary, as it`
  line `may consider necessary;`
  line
  line `(b) require an insurer to submit for its examination at the principal place of business of the insurer`
  line `in India, any books of account, register or other document, or to supply any statement which may be`
  line `specified in the notice;`
  line
  line `(c) examine any officer of an insurer on oath, in relation to any such information, book, register,`
  line `document or statement and the insurer, shall comply with any such requirement within such time as`
  line `may be specified in the notice.]`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (18181)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 87
  title `Policy not to be called in question on ground of mis-statement after two years.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 55, ibid., for sections 44A and 45 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18181&sectionno=45&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) No policy`
  line `of life insurance shall be called in question on any ground whatsoever after the expiry of three years from`
  line `the date of the policy, i.e., from the date of issuance of the policy or the date of commencement of risk or`
  line `the date of revival of the policy or the date of the rider to the policy, whichever is later.`
  line
  line `(2) A policy of life insurance may be called in question at any time within three years from the date of`
  line `issuance of the policy or the date of commencement of risk or the date of revival of the policy or the date`
  line `of the rider to the policy, whichever is later, on the ground of fraud:`
  line
  line `Provided that the insurer shall have to communicate in writing to the insured or the legal`
  line `representatives or nominees or assignees of the insured the grounds and materials on which such decision`
  line `is based.`
  line
  line `Explanation I. --For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "fraud" means any of the`
  line `following acts committed by the insured or by his agent, with intent to deceive the insurer or to induce the`
  line `insurer to issue a life insurance policy: --`
  line
  line `(a) the suggestion, as a fact of that which is not true and which the insured does not believe to be`
  line true;
  line
  line `(b) the active concealment of a fact by the insured having knowledge or belief of the fact;`
  line
  line `(c) any other act fitted to deceive; and`
  line
  line `(d) any such act or omission as the law specially declares to be fraudulent.`
  line
  line `Explanation II. --Mere silence as to facts likely to affect the assessment of the risk by the insurer is`
  line `not fraud, unless the circumstances of the case are such that regard being had to them, it is the duty of the`
  line `insured or his agent keeping silence, to speak, or unless his silence is, in itself, equivalent to speak.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), no insurer shall repudiate a life insurance`
  line `policy on the ground of fraud if the insured can prove that the misstatement of or suppression of a`
  line `material fact was true to the best of his knowledge and belief or that there was no deliberate intention to`
  line `suppress the fact or that such misstatement of or suppression of a material fact are within the knowledge`
  line `of the insurer:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of fraud, the onus of disproving lies upon the beneficiaries, in case the`
  line `policyholder is not alive.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --A person who solicits and negotiates a contract of insurance shall be deemed for the`
  line `purpose of the formation of the contract, to be the agent of the insurer.`
  line
  line `(4) A policy of life insurance may be called in question at any time within three years from the date of`
  line `issuance of the policy or the date of commencement of risk or the date of revival of the policy or the date`
  line `of the rider to the policy, whichever is later, on the ground that any statement of or suppression of a fact`
  line `material to the expectancy of the life of the insured was incorrectly made in the proposal or other`
  line `document on the basis of which the policy was issued or revived or rider issued:`
  line
  line `Provided that the insurer shall have to communicate in writing to the insured or the legal`
  line `representatives or nominees or assignees of the insured the grounds and materials on which such decision`
  line `to repudiate the policy of life insurance is based:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of repudiation of the policy on the ground of misstatement or`
  line `suppression of a material fact, and not on the ground of fraud, the premiums collected on the policy till`
  line `the date of repudiation shall be paid to the insured or the legal representatives or nominees or assignees of`
  line `the insured within a period of ninety days from the date of such repudiation.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --For the purposes of this sub-section, the misstatement of or suppression of fact shall`
  line `not be considered material unless it has a direct bearing on the risk undertaken by the insurer, the onus is`
  line `on the insurer to show that had the insurer been aware of the said fact no life insurance policy would have`
  line `been issued to the insured.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall prevent the insurer from calling for proof of age at any time if he is`
  line `entitled to do so, and no policy shall be deemed to be called in question merely because the terms of the`
  line `policy are adjusted on subsequent proof that the age of the life insured was incorrectly stated in the`
  line proposal.]
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (18182)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 88
  title `Application of the law in force in India to policies issued in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18182&sectionno=46&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The holder of a policy of`
  line `insurance issued by an insurer in respect of insurance business transacted in ^1[India] after the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall have the right, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the`
  line `policy or in any agreement relating thereto, to receive payment in ^1[India], of any sum secured thereby`
  line `and to sue for any relief in respect of the policy in any Court of competent jurisdiction in ^1[India]; and if`
  line `the suit is brought in ^1[India]; any question of law arising in connection with any such policy shall be`
  line `determined according to the law in force in ^1[India]:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a policy of marine insurance.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the First Schedule, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 7 of 1944, s. 2 (w.e.f. 7-3-1944).`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (18183)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 89
  title `Payment of money into Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18183&sectionno=47&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in respect of any policy of life insurance maturing`
  line `for payment an insurer is of opinion that by reason of conflicting claims to or insufficiency of proof of`
  line `title to the amount secured thereby or for any other adequate reason it is impossible otherwise for the`
  line `insurer to obtain a satisfactory discharge for the payment of such amount, ^1[the insurer may], ^2[***] apply to pay the amount into the Court within the jurisdiction of which is situated the place at which such`
  line `amount is payable under the terms of the policy or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(2) A receipt granted by the Court for any such payment shall be a satisfactory discharge to the`
  line `insurer for the payment of such amount.`
  line
  line `(3) An application for permission to make a payment into Court under this section shall be made by a`
  line `petition verified by an affidavit signed by a principal officer of the insurer setting forth the following`
  line `particulars, namely: --`
  line
  line `(a) the name of the insured person and his address;`
  line
  line `(b) if the insured person is deceased, the date and place of hi s death;`
  line
  line `(c) the nature of the policy and the amount secured by it;`
  line
  line `(d) the name and address of each claimant so far as is known to the insurer with details of every`
  line `notice of claim received;`
  line
  line `(e) the reasons why in the opinion of the insurer a satisfactory discharged cannot be obtained for`
  line `the payment of the amount; and`
  line
  line `(f) the address at which the insurer may be served with notice of any proceeding relating to`
  line `disposal of the amount paid into Court.`
  line
  line `(4) An application under this section shall not be entertained by the Court if the application is made`
  line `before the expiry of six months ^3[from the maturing of the policy by survival, or from the date of receipt`
  line `of notice by the insurer of the death of the insured, as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `(5) If it appears to the Court that a satisfactory discharge for the payment of the amount cannot`
  line `otherwise be obtained by the insurer it shall allow the amount to be paid into Court and shall invest the`
  line `amount in Government securities pending its disposal.`
  line
  line `(6) The Insurer shall transmit to the Court every notice of claim received after the making of the`
  line `application under sub-section (3), and any payment required by the Court as costs of the proceedings or`
  line `otherwise in connection with the disposal of the amount paid into Court shall as to the cost of the`
  line `application under sub-section (3) be borne by the insurer and as to any other costs be in the discretion of`
  line `the Court.`
  line
  line `(7) The Court shall cause notice to be given to every ascertained claimant of the fact that the amount`
  line `has been paid into Court, and shall cause notice at the cost of any claimant applying to withdraw the`
  line `amount to be given to every other ascertained claimant.`
  line
  line `(8) The Court shall decide all questions relating to the disposal of claims to the amount paid into`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 1941, s. 32, for "the insurer shall" (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line
  line `2. Certain words omitted by Act 47 of 1950, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 11 of 1939, s. 18, for "from the death of the insured, or the maturing of the policy by survival".`
