  line `[Appointment of additional directors].-- [Omitted by the Insurance (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1968 (62 of 1968), s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-6-1969)].]`
obj_root_law_sections_48_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (18189)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 95
  title `Restriction On dividends and bonuses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18189&sectionno=49&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `^2[49. Restriction on dividends and bonuses. --^3[(1)] No insurer, ^4***, who carries on the business`
  line `of life insurance or any other class or sub-class of insurance business to which section 13 applies, shall,`
  line `for the purpose of declaring or paying any dividend to shareholders or any bonus to policy-holders or of`
  line `making any payment in service of any debentures, utilize directly or indirectly any portion of the life`
  line `insurance fund or of the fund of such other class or sub-class of insurance business, as the case may be,`
  line `except a surplus shown in the valuation ^5[balance-sheet in such form as may be specified by the`
  line `regulations made by the Authority] submitted to the ^1[Authority] as part of the abstract referred to in`
  line `section 15 as a result of an actuarial valuation of the assets and liabilities of the insurer; nor shall he`
  line `increase such surplus by contributions out of any reserve fund or otherwise unless such contributions have`
  line `been brought in as revenue account applicable to that class or sub-class of insurance business on or before`
  line `the date of the valuation aforesaid, except when the reserve fund is made up solely of transfers from`
  line `similar surpluses disclosed by valuations in respect of which returns have been submitted to the`
  line `^1[Authority] under section 15 of this Act ^6***:`
  line
  line `Provided that payments made out of any such surplus in service of any debentures shall not exceed`
  line `fifty percent, of such surplus including any payment by way of interest on the debentures, and interest`
  line `paid on the debentures shall not exceed ten per cent, of any such surplus except when the interest paid on`
  line `the debentures is offset against the interest credited to the fund or funds concerned in deciding the interest`
  line `basis adopted in the valuation disclosing the aforesaid surplus:]`
  line
  line `^7[Provided further that the share of any such surplus allocated to or reserved for the shareholders,`
  line `(including any amount for the payment of dividends guaranteed to them, whether by way of first charge`
  line `or otherwise), shall not exceed such sums as may be specified by the Authority and such share shall in no`
  line `case exceed ten per cent of such surplus in case of participating policies and in other cases the whole`
  line thereof.]
  line
  line `^8[(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the actual amount of income-tax deducted at source during`
  line `the period following the date as at which the last preceding valuation was made and preceding the date as`
  line `at which the valuation in question is made may be added to such surplus after deducting an estimated`
  line `amount for income-tax on such surplus, such addition and deduction being shown in ^9[an abstract of the`
  line `report of the actuary referred to in sub-section (1) of section 13].]`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1941, s. 34, for section 49 (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line
  line `3. Section 49 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 47 of 1950, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
  line
  line `4. The words, brackets, letters and figures "being an insurer specified in sub-clause (a) (ii) or sub-clause (b) of clause (9) of`
  line `section 2" omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 58 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 42 of 2002, s. 12, for "balance sheet in Form I as set forth in the Fourth Schedule" (w.e.f. 23-9-2002).`
  line
  line `6. The words and figures "or to the Central Government under section 11 of the Indian Life Insurance Companies Act, 1912 (7 of`
  line `1912)" Omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 58 (w.e.f. 26.12.2014).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 42 of 2002, s. 12, for the second proviso (w.e.f. 23-9-2002).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 47 of 1950, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 42 of 2002, s. 12, for "paragraph 8(1) of the abstract prepared in accordance with Part II of the Fourth Schedule`
  line `to this Act" (w.e.f. 23-9-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (18190)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 96
  title `Notice of options available to the assured on the lapsing of a policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18190&sectionno=50&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `An insurer shall,`
  line `^1[before the expiry of three months from the date on which the premiums in respect of a policy of life`
  line `insurance were payable but not paid], give notice to the policy-holder informing hi m of the options`
  line `available to him ^2[unless these are set forth in the policy.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 11 of 1939, s. 20, for "within three months of the lapsing of policy of life insurance".`
  line
  line `2 Added by Act 13 of 1941, s. 35 (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (18191)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 97
  title `Supply of copies of proposals and medical reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18191&sectionno=51&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Every insurer shall, on application by a`
  line `policy-holder and on payment of a fee not exceeding one rupee, supply to the policy-holder certified`
  line `copies of the question put to him and his answers thereto contained in his proposal for insurance and in`
  line `the medical report supplied in connection therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (18192)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 98
  title `Prohibition of business of dividing principle.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 59, for sections 52 and 52A (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18192&sectionno=52&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `^1[52. Prohibition of business on dividing principle. -- No insurer shall commence any business`
  line `upon the dividing principle, that is to say, on the principle that the benefit secured by a policy is not fixed`
  line `but depends either wholly or partly on the result of a distribution of certain sums amongst policies`
  line `becoming claims within certain time-limits, or on the principle that the premiums payable by a`
  line `policyholder depend wholly or partly on the number of policies becoming claims within certain timelimits:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent an insurer from allocating bonuses to`
  line `holders of policies of life insurance as a result of a periodical actuarial valuation either as reversionary`
  line `additions to the sums insured or as immediate cash bonuses or otherwise.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_a:
  sectionId (18193)
  sectionNo 52A
  orderNo 99
  title `When Administrator for management of insurance business may be appointed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 1950, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18193&sectionno=52A&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[52A. When Administrator for management of insurance business may be appointed. --(1) If at`
  line `any time the Authority has reason to believe that an insurer carrying on life insurance business is acting in`
  line `a manner likely to be prejudicial to the interests of holders of life insurance policies, it may, after giving`
  line `such opportunity to the insurer to be heard appoint an Administrator to manage the affairs of the insurer`
  line `under the direction and control of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator shall receive such remuneration as the Authority may direct and the Authority`
  line `may at any time cancel the appointment and appoint some other person as Administrator.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_b:
  sectionId (18194)
  sectionNo 52B
  orderNo 100
  title `Powers and duties of the Administrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18194&sectionno=52B&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_52_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator shall conduct the`
  line `management of the business of the insurer with the greatest economy compatible with efficiency and`
  line `shall, as soon as may be possible, file with the ^2[Authority] a report stating which of the following courses is in the circumstances most advantageous to the general interests of the holders of life insurance policies,`
  line `namely: --`
  line
  line `(a) the transfer of the business of the insurer to some other insurer;`
  line
  line `(b) the carrying on of its business by the insurer (whether with the policies of the business continued`
  line `for the original, sum insured with the addition of bonuses that attach to the policies or for reduced`
  line `amounts);`
  line
  line `(c) the winding up of the insurer; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other course as he deems advisable.`
  line
  line `(2) On the filing of the report with the ^1[Authority], the ^1[Authority] may take such action as he thinks`
  line `fit for promoting the interests of the holders of life insurance policies in general.`
  line
  line `(3) Any order passed by the ^1[Authority] under sub-section (2) shall be binding on all persons`
  line `concerned, and shall have effect notwithstanding anything in the memorandum or articles of association`
  line `of the insurer, of a company.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_52_bb:
  sectionId (18195)
  sectionNo 52BB
  orderNo 101
  title `Powers of Administrator respecting property liable to attachment under section 106.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_bb_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_bb_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18195&sectionno=52BB&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_52_bb_content:
  string
  line `^1[52BB. Powers of Administrator respecting property liable to attachment under`
  line `section 106. -- (1) If the Administrator is satisfied that any person has rendered himself liable to be`
  line `proceeded against under section 106, he may, pending the institution of proceedings against such person`
  line `under that section, by order in writing, prohibit him or any other person from transferring or otherwise`
  line `disposing of any property which, in the opinion of the Administrator, would be liable to attachment in`
  line `proceedings under that section.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by an order made by the Administrator under sub-section (1) may, within`
  line `fourteen days from the date on which the order is served on him, appeal against such order to ^2[the`
  line `Securities Appellate Tribunal and the Securities Appellate Tribunal] may pass such order thereon as it`
  line `thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) An order made by the Administrator under sub-section (1) shall, subject to any other order made`
  line `by the ^3[Securities Appellate Tribunal] on appeal, be in force for a period of three months from the date of`
  line `of the order unless, before the expiry of the said period, an application is made under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 106 to the Court competent to exercise jurisdiction under that sub-section, and when such an`
  line `application is made, the order shall, subject to any order made by that Court, continue in force as if it`
  line `were an order of attachment made by that Court in proceedings under that section.`
  line
  line `(4) An order made by the Administrator under this section shall, --`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an order affecting a corporation or firm, be served in the manner provided for`
  line `the service of summons in rule 2 of Order XXIX or rule 3 of Order XXX, as the case may be, in the`
  line `First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an order affecting a person not being a corporation or firm, be served on such`
  line person--
  line
  line `(i) personally, by delivering or tendering to him the order, or`
  line
  line `(ii) by post, or`
  line
  line `(iii) where the person cannot be found, by leaving a copy of the order with some adult male`
  line `member of his family or by affixing such copy to some conspicuous part of the premises in which`
  line `he is known to have last resided or carried on business or personally worked for gain,`
  line `and every such order shall also be published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(5) If any question arises whether a person was duly served with an order under sub-section (4), the`
  line `publication of the order in the Official Gazette shall be conclusive proof that the order was so served, and`
  line `a failure to comply with the provisions of clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (4) shall not affect the`
  line `validity of the order.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, any property in respect of which an order has`
  line `been made by the Administrator may, with the previous permission of the Administrator and subject to`
  line `such terms and conditions as he may impose, be transferred or otherwise disposed of.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the transfer or`
  line `other disposition of any property in contravention of any order made by the Administrator under this`
  line `section or of any terms and conditions imposed by him shall be void.`
  line
  line `(8) For the purpose of enabling him to form an option as to whether any property would be liable to`
  line `attachment in proceedings under section 106 or for the purpose of enabling him to institute proceedings`
  line `under that section, the Administrator may require any person to furnish information on such points or`
  line `matters as, in the opinion of the Administrator, may be relevant for the purpose, and any person so`
  line `required shall be deemed to be legally bound to furnish such information within the meaning of section`
  line `176 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(9) The Administrator shall have all the powers of a Civil Court under the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely: --`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing attendance of witnesses and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the production of documents; and`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits.`
  line
  line `and any proceeding before the Administrator under this section shall be deemed to be a judicial`
  line `proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228 of Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(10) Save as provided in this section or in section 106, and notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, --`
  line
  line `(a) no suit or other legal proceeding shall lie in any Court to set aside or modify any order of the`
  line `Administrator ^4*** made under this section, and`
  line
  line `(b) no Court shall pass any decree, grant any injunction or make any other order which shall have`
  line `the effect of nullifying or affection in any way any such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_bb_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 54 of 1955, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 60, for "the Central Government and the Central Government" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 60, ibid., for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `4. The words "or the Central Government" omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 60 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014)`
obj_root_law_sections_52_c:
  sectionId (18196)
  sectionNo 52C
  orderNo 102
  title `Cancellation of contracts and agreements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18196&sectionno=52C&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_52_c_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator may, at any time during the`
  line `continuance of his appointment with respect to an insurer and after giving an opportunity to the persons`
  line `concerned to be heard, cancel or vary (either unconditionally or subject to such conditions as he thinks fit`
  line `to impose) any contract or agreement (other than a policy) between the insurer and any other person`
  line `which the Administrator is satisfied is prejudicial to the interest of holders of life insurance policies.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52_d:
  sectionId (18197)
  sectionNo 52D
  orderNo 103
  title `Termination of appointment of Administrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 61, ibid., for section 52D (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18197&sectionno=52D&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_52_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[52D. Termination of appointment of Administrator. --If at any time, it appears to the Authority`
  line `that the purpose of the order appointing the Administrator has been fulfilled or that, for any reason, it is undesirable that the order of appointment should remain in force, the Authority may cancel the order and`
  line `thereupon the Administrator shall be divested of the management of the insurance business which shall,`
  line `unless otherwise directed by the Authority, again vest in the person in whom it was vested immediately`
  line `prior to the appointment of the Administrator or any other person appointed by the insurer in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_e:
  sectionId (18198)
  sectionNo 52E
  orderNo 104
  title `Finality of decision appointing Administrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_e_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 62, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18198&sectionno=52E&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_52_e_content:
  string
  line `Any order or decision of the ^1[Authority]`
  line `made in pursuance of section 52A or section 52D shall be final and shall not be called in question in any`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_52_f:
  sectionId (18199)
  sectionNo 52F
  orderNo 105
  title `Penalty for withholding documents or property from Administrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18199&sectionno=52F&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_52_f_content:
  string
  line `If any director or`
  line `officer of the insurer or any other person fails to deliver to the Administrator any books of account,`
  line `registers or any other documents, in his custody relating to the business of the insurer the management of`
  line `which has vested in the Administrator, or retains any property of such insurer he shall be ^1[liable to`
  line `penalty of rupees ten thousand each day during which such failure continues or rupees ten lakh,`
  line `whichever is less].]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_f_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 63, ibid., for "punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to`
  line `one thousand rupees, or with both" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_52_g:
  sectionId (18200)
  sectionNo 52G
  orderNo 106
  title `Protection of action taken under sections 52A to 52D.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_g_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_g_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18200&sectionno=52G&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_52_g_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other`
  line `legal proceeding shall lie against an Administrator for anything which is in good faith done or intended to`
  line `be done in pursuance of ^1[section 52A, section 52B, section 52BB or section 52C].`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the ^2*** the ^3[Authority] for any damage caused`
  line `or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done of intended to be done under section 52A,`
  line `section 52B, or section 52D.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_g_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1955, s. 3, for "sections 52A to 52C inclusive" (w.e.f. 1-11-1955).`
  line
  line `2. The words "Central Government or" omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 64 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs .by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
