obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (18208)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 114
  title `Winding up by the Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18208&sectionno=53&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Tribunal may order the winding up in accordance with`
  line `the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) of any insurance company and the provisions of that Act shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of this Act, apply accordingly.]`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation. --For the purpose of sections 53 to 61A, "Tribunal" means the National Company`
  line `Law Tribunal constituted under sub-section (1) of section 408 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013).]`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the grounds on which such an order may be based, the ^3[Tribunal] may order the`
  line `winding up of an insurance company--`
  line
  line `(a) if with the sanction of the ^3[Tribunal] previously obtained a petition in this behalf is presented`
  line `by shareholders not less in number than one tenth of the whole body of shareholders and holding not`
  line `less than one-tenth of the whole share capital or by not less than fifty policy-holders holding policies`
  line `of life insurance that have been in force for not less than three years and are of the total value of not`
  line `less than fifty thousand rupees; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the ^4[Authority], who is hereby authorised to do so, applies in this behalf of the ^3[Tribunal]`
  line `on any of the following grounds, namely: --`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(ii) that the company having failed to comply with any requirement of this Act has continued`
  line `such failure ^6[or having contravened any provision of this Act has continued such contravention]`
  line `for a period of three months after notice of such failure ^6[or contravention] has been conveyed to`
  line `the company by the ^4[Authority],`
  line
  line `(iii) that it appears from ^7[any returns or statements] furnished under the provisions of this`
  line `Act or from the results of any investigation made thereunder that the ^8[company is, or is deemed`
  line `to be insolvent], or`
  line
  line `(iv) that the continuance of the company is prejudicial to the interest of the policy-holders ^9[or`
  line `to the public interest generally].`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 11 of 2003, s. 133 and the Schedule, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 66 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 11 of 2003, s. 133 and the Schedule serial No. 2 (b), for "Court" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `4 Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `5. Sub-clause (i) omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 66 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `6 Ins. by Act 13 of 1941, s. 37 (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line
  line `7 Subs. by Act 62 or 1968, s. 23, for "the returns" (w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
  line
  line `8 Subs. by s. 23, ibid. for "company is insolvent" (w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
  line
  line `9 Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
obj_root_law_sections_53_a:
  sectionId (18209)
  sectionNo 53A
  orderNo 115
  title `Unpaid-up share capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1946, s. 25 (w.e.f. 20-3-1946).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18209&sectionno=53A&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[53A. Unpaid-up share capital.--Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, in`
  line `ascertaining for any purpose of this Act the solvency or otherwise of an insurer no account shall be taken`
  line `of any assets of the insurer consisting of unpaid up share capital.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (18210)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 116
  title `Voluntary winding up.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 2003, s. 133 and the Schedule, for "Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913)" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18210&sectionno=54&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the ^1[Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956)], an insurance company shall not be wound up voluntarily except for the purpose of`
  line `affecting an amalgamation or a re-construction of the company, or on the ground that by reason of its`
  line `liabilities it cannot continue its business.`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (18211)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 117
  title `Valuation of liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18211&sectionno=55&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the winding up of an insurance company or in the insolvency of`
  line `any other insurer the value of the assets and the liabilities of the insurer shall be ascertained in such`
  line `manner and upon such basis as the liquidator or receiver in insolvency thinks fit, subject, so far as`
  line `applicable, to the rule contained in the ^1[Seventh Schedule] and to any directions which may be given by`
  line `the ^2[Tribunal].`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of any reduction by the ^3[Tribunal] of the amount of the contracts of any`
  line `insurance company the value of the assets and liabilities of the company and all claims in respect of`
  line `policies issued by it shall be ascertained in such manner and upon such basis as the ^3[Tribunal] thinks`
  line `proper having regard to the aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) The rule in the ^4[Seventh Schedule] shall be of the same force and may be repealed, altered or`
  line `amended as if it were a rule made in pursuance of ^5[section 643 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)],`
  line `and rules may be made under that section for the purpose of carrying into effect the provisions of this Act`
  line `with respect to the winding up of insurance companies.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1950, s. 43, for "Sixth Schedule" (w.e.f. 1-9-1950).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 2003, s. 133 and the Schedule Serial no. 4 (a), for "Court" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 2003, s. 133 and the Schedule serial no. 4(a), for "Court" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 47 of 1950, s. 43, for "Sixth Schedule" (w.e.f. 1-9-1950).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 11 of 2003, s. 133 and the Schedule, for "Section 246 of the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913)"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (18212)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 118
  title `Application of surplus assets of life insurance fund in liquidation or insolvency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 133 and the Schedule (serial no. 5), ibid., for "Court" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18212&sectionno=56&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the`
  line `winding up of an insurance company and in the insolvency of any other insurer the value of the assets and`
  line `the liabilities of the insurer in respect of life insurance business shall be ascertained separately from the`
  line `value of any other assets or any other liabilities of the insurer and no such assets shall be applied to the`
  line `discharge of any liabilities other than those in respect of life insurance business except in so far as those`
  line `assets exceed the liabilities in respect of life insurance business.`
  line
  line `(2) In the winding up of an insurance company carrying on the business of life insurance or in the`
  line `insolvency of any other insurer carrying on such business where any proportion of the profits of the`
  line `insurer was before the commencement of the winding up or insolvency allocated to policy-holders if,`
  line `when the assets and liabilities of the insurer have been ascertained, there is found to be a surplus of assets`
  line `over liabilities (hereinafter referred to as a prima facie surplus) there shall be added to the liabilities of the`
  line `insurer in respect of the life insurance business an amount equal to such proportion of the prima facie`
  line `surplus as is equivalent to such proportion of the profits allocated to shareholders and policy-holders as`
  line `was allocated to policy-holders during the ten years immediately preceding the commencement of the`
  line `winding up and the assets of the insurer shall be deemed to exceed his liabilities only in so far as those`
  line `assets exceed those liabilities after such addition:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) if in any case there has been no such allocation or if it appears to the ^1[Tribunal] that by reason of`
  line `special circumstances it would be inequitable that the amount to be added to the liabilities of the insurer`
  line `in respect of the life insurance business should be an amount equal to such proportion as aforesaid, the`
  line `amount to be so added shall be such amount as the ^1[Tribunal] may direct, and`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of the application of this sub-section to any case where before the commencement`
  line `of the winding up or insolvency a proportion of such profits as aforesaid of a branch only of the life`
  line `insurance business in question has been allocated to policy-holders, the value of the assets and liabilities`
  line `of the insurer in respect of that branch shall be separately ascertained in like manner as the value of his`
  line `assets and liabilities in respect of the life insurance business was ascertained, and the surplus so found, if`
  line `any, of assets over liabilities shall, for the purpose of determining the amount to be added to the liabilities`
  line `of the insurer in respect of the life insurance business be deemed to be the prima facie surplus.`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (18213)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 119
  title `Winding up of secondary companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18213&sectionno=57&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the insurance business or any part of the`
  line `insurance business of an insurance company has been transferred to another insurance company under an`
  line `arrangement in pursuance of which the first mentioned company (in this section referred to as the`
  line `secondary company) or the creditors thereof has or have claims against the company to which such`
  line `transfer was made (in this section referred to as the principal company) then, if the principal company is`
  line `being wound up by ^1***, the ^2[Tribunal] shall (subject as hereinafter mentioned) order the secondary`
  line `company to be wound up in conjunction with the principal company and may by the same or any`
  line `subsequent order appoint the same person to be liquidator for the two companies and make provision for`
  line `such other matters as may seem to the ^2[Tribunal] necessary with a view to the companies being wound`
  line `up as if they were one company.`
  line
  line `(2) The commencement of the winding up of the principal company shall, save as otherwise ordered`
  line `by the ^2[Tribunal], be the commencement of the winding up of the secondary company.`
  line
  line `(3) In adjusting the rights and liabilities of the members of the several companies among themselves`
  line `the ^2[Tribunal], shall have regard to the constitution of the companies and to the arrangements entered`
  line `into between the companies in the same manner as the ^2[Tribunal], has regard to the rights and liabilities`
  line `of different classes of contributories in the case of winding up of a single company or as near thereto as`
  line `circumstances admit.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any company alleged to be secondary is not in process of being wound up at the same time`
  line `as the principal company to which it is alleged to be secondary, the ^2[Tribunal] shall not direct the`
  line `secondary company to be wound up, unless, after hearing all objections (if any) that may be urged by or`
  line `on behalf of the company against its being wound up, the ^2[Tribunal] is of opinion that the company is`
  line `secondary to the principal company and that the winding up of the company in conjunction with the`
  line `principal company is just and equitable.`
  line
  line `(5) An application may be made in relation to the winding up of any secondary company in`
  line `conjunction with the principal company by any creditor of, or person interested in, the principal or`
  line `secondary company.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a company stands in the relation of a principal company to one insurance company and in`
  line `the relation of a secondary company to some other insurance company or where there are several`
  line `insurance companies standing in the relation of secondary companies to one principal company,`
  line `the ^2[Tribunal] may deal with any number of such companies together or in separate groups as it thinks`
  line `most expedient upon the principles laid down in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The Words "or under the supervision of the Court" omitted by Act 11 of 2003, s. 133 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `2/ Subs. by s. 133 and the Schedule serial no. 6(b), ibid., for "Court" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (18214)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 120
  title `Schemes for partial winding up of insurance companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18214&sectionno=58&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time it appears`
  line `expedient that the affairs of an insurance company in respect of any class of business comprised in the`
  line `undertaking of the company should be wound up but that any other class of business comprised the`
  line `undertaking should continue to be carried on by the company or be transferred to another insurer, a`
  line `scheme for such purposes may be prepared and submitted for confirmation of the ^1[Tribunal] in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any scheme prepared under this section shall provide for the allocation and distribution of the`
  line `assets and liabilities of the company between any classes of business affected (including the allocation of`
  line `any surplus assets which may arise on the proposed winding up), for any future rights of every class of`
  line `policy-holders in respect of their policies and for the manner of winding up any of the affairs of the`
  line `company which are proposed to be wound up and may contain provisions for altering the memorandum`
  line `of the company with respect to its objects and such further provisions as may be expedient for giving`
  line `effect to the scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this Act relating to the valuation of liabilities of insurers in liquidation and`
  line `insolvency and to the application of surplus assets of the life insurance fund in liquidation or insolvency`
  line `shall apply to the winding up of any part of the affairs of a company in accordance with the scheme under`
  line `this section in like manner as they apply in the winding up of an insurance company, and any scheme under this section may apply with the necessary modifications any of the provisions of the Indian`
  line `Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913) relating to the winding up of companies.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) An order of the Tribunal confirming a scheme under this section whereby the memorandum of a`
  line `company is altered with respect to its objects shall as respects the alteration have effect as if it were an`
  line `order confirmed under section 4 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), and the provisions of sections`
  line `7 and 17 of that Act shall apply accordingly.]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 133 and the Schedule (serial no. 7), ibid., for "Court" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 67, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (5) omitted by Act 62 of 1968, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (18215)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 121
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18215&sectionno=59&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
