  string
  line `[Return of deposits].-- Omitted by the Insurance Laws (Amendment) Act 5 of 2015, s. 68`
  line `(w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (18216)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 122
  title `Notice of policy values.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 2003, s. 133 and the Schedule (serial no. 7), for "Court" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18216&sectionno=60&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `In the winding up of an insurance company for the purposes of a`
  line `cash distribution of the assets and in the insolvency of any other insurer the liquidator or assignee as the`
  line `case may be in the case of all persons appearing by the books of the company or other insurer to be`
  line `entitled to or interested in the policies granted by the company or other insurer shall ascertain the value of`
  line `the liability of the company or other insurer to each such person and shall give notice of such value to`
  line `those persons in such manner as the ^1[Tribunal] may direct and any person to whom notice is so given`
  line `shall be bound by the value so ascertained unless he gives notice of his intention to dispute such value in`
  line `such manner and within such time as may be specified by a rule or order of the ^1[Tribunal].`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (18217)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 123
  title `Power of Court to reduce contracts of insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18217&sectionno=61&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `61. Power of ^1[Tribunal] to reduce contracts of insurance. --(1) Where an insurance company is`
  line `in liquidation or any other insurer is insolvent the ^1[Tribunal] may make an order reducing the amount of`
  line `the insurance contracts of the company or other insurer upon such terms and subject to such conditions as`
  line `the ^1[Tribunal] thinks just.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a company carrying on the business of life insurance has been proved to be insolvent,`
  line `the ^1[Tribunal] may if it thinks fit in place of making a winding up order reduce the amount of the`
  line `insurance contracts of the company upon such terms and subject to such conditions as the ^1[Tribunal]`
  line `thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Application for an order under this section may be made either by the liquidator or by or on behalf`
  line `of the company or by a policy-holder, or by the ^2[Authority] and by any person whom the ^1[Tribunal]`
  line `thinks likely to be affected shall be entitled to be heard on any such application.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 2003, s. 133 and the Schedule (serial no. 7), for "Court" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_61_a:
  sectionId (18218)
  sectionNo 61A
  orderNo 124
  title `Appeal to National Company Law Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2003, s. 133 and the schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18218&sectionno=61A&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_61_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[61A. Appeal to National Company Law Appellate Tribunal. -- (1) Any person aggrieved by an`
  line `order or decision of the Tribunal may prefer an appeal to the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie to the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal from an order made by the`
  line `Tribunal with the consent of parties.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of forty-five days from the date`
  line `on which a copy of the order or decision made by the Tribunal is received by the appellant and it shall be`
  line `in such from and accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Provided that the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry`
  line `of said period of forty-five days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that`
  line period.
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal`
  line `shall, after giving parties to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it`
  line `thinks fit, confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(5) The National Company Law Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the`
  line `Tribunal and parties to the appeal.`
  line
  line `(6) The appeal filed before the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `be dealt with by it as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal`
  line `finally within six months from the date of the receipt of the appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (18219)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 125
  title `Power of Central Government to impose reciprocal disabilities on non-Indian companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18219&sectionno=62&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Where, by the law or practice of any country outside India in which an insurer carrying on insurance`
  line `business in ^1[India] is constituted, incorporated or domiciled, insurance companies incorporated in`
  line `^1[India] are required as a condition of carrying on insurance business in that country to comply with any`
  line `special requirement whether as to the keeping of deposits or assets in that country or otherwise which is`
  line `not imposed upon insurers of that country under this Act, the Central Government shall, if satisfied of the`
  line `existence of such special requirement, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the same`
  line `requirement, or requirements as similar thereto as may be, shall be imposed upon insurers of that country`
  line `as a condition of carrying on the business of insurance in ^1[India].`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (18220)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 126
  title `Particulars to be filed by insurers established outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18220&sectionno=63&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Every insurer, having his`
  line `principal place of business or domicile outside ^1[India] who establishes a place of business within ^1[India]`
  line `or appoints a ^2[representative] in ^1[India] with the object of obtaining insurance business, shall, within`
  line `three months from the establishment of such place of business or the appointment of`
  line `such ^2[representative], file with the ^3[Authority] --`
  line
  line `(a) a certified copy of the charter, statutes, deed of settlement or memorandum and articles or`
  line `other instrument constituting or defining the constitution of the insurer, and, if the instrument is not`
  line `written in the English language, a certified translation thereof,`
  line
  line `(b) a list of the directors, if the insurer is a company,`
  line
  line `(c) the name and address of some or more persons resident in ^1[India] authorised to accept on`
  line `behalf of the insurer service of process and any notice required to be served on the insurer, together`
  line `with a copy of the power-of-attorney granted to him,`
  line
  line `(d) the full address of the principal office of the insurer in ^1[India].,`
  line
  line `(e) a statement of the classes of insurance business to be carried on by the insurer, and`
  line
  line `(f) a statement verified by an affidavit setting forth the special requirements, if any, of the nature`
  line `specified in section 62 imposed in the country of origin of the insurer on Indian nationals,`
  line `and, in the event of any alteration being made in the address of the principal office or in the classes of`
  line `business to be carried on, or in any instrument here referred to, or in the name of any of the persons here`
  line `referred to, or in the matters specified in clause (f) above, the company shall forthwith furnish to`
  line `the ^3[Authority] particulars of such alteration.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1939, s. 23, for "agent".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (18221)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 127
  title `Books to be kept by insurers established outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18221&sectionno=64&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Every insurer, having his principal`
  line `place of business or domicile outside ^1[India]., Shall keep at his principal office in ^1[India]. such books of`
  line `account, registers and documents as will enable the accounts, statements and abstracts which he is`
  line `required under this Act to furnish to the ^2[Authority] in respect of the insurance business transacted by`
  line `him, in India to be compiled and, if necessary, checked by the ^2[Authority] ^3[and shall furnish to`
  line `the ^2[Authority] on or before the last day of January in every calendar year a certificate from an auditor to the effect that the said books of account, register and documents are being kept as required at the principal`
  line `office of the insurer in India].`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Added by Act 47 of 1950, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-6-1950).`
obj_root_law_sections_64_a:
  sectionId (18222)
  sectionNo 64A
  orderNo 128
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_a_content
