obj_root_law_sections_64_c:
  sectionId (18224)
  sectionNo 64C
  orderNo 130
  title `Councils of Life Insurance and General Insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 71, ibid., for sections 64C and 64D (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18224&sectionno=64C&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[64C. Councils of Life Insurance and General Insurance.--On and from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act, --`
  line
  line `(a) the existing Life Insurance Council, a representative body of the insurers, who carry on the`
  line `life insurance business in India; and`
  line
  line `(b) the existing General Insurance Council, a representative body of insurers, who carry on`
  line `general, health insurance business and re-insurance in India,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to have been constituted as the respective Councils under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_d:
  sectionId (18225)
  sectionNo 64D
  orderNo 131
  title `Authorisation to represent in Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 71, ibid., for sections 64C and 64D (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18225&sectionno=64D&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[64D. Authorisation to represent in Councils.--It shall be lawful for any member of the Life`
  line `Insurance Council or the General Insurance Council to authorise any of its officer to act as the`
  line `representative of such member at any meeting of the Council concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_e:
  sectionId (18226)
  sectionNo 64E
  orderNo 132
  title `Authorities of the Life Insurance Council and the General Insurance Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_e_content
  footnotes `1. The words "the Tariff Committee and other Committee thereof" omitted by Act 62 of 1968, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18226&sectionno=64E&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_e_content:
  string
  line The
  line `authorities of the Life Insurance Council and the General Insurance Council shall be the Executive`
  line `Committee ^1*** constituted in the manner provided in this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_f:
  sectionId (18227)
  sectionNo 64F
  orderNo 133
  title `Executive Committees of the Life Insurance Council and the General Insurance Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_f_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 72, for section 64F (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18227&sectionno=64F&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[64F. Executive Committees of the Life Insurance Council and the General Insurance`
  line `Council.--(1) The Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council shall consist of the following`
  line `persons, namely: --`
  line
  line `(a) four representatives of members of the Life Insurance Council elected in their individual`
  line `capacity by the members in such manner as may be laid down in the bye-laws of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) an eminent person not connected with insurance business, nominated by the Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) three persons to represent insurance agents, intermediaries and policyholders respectively as`
  line `may be nominated by the Authority;`
  line
  line `(d) one representative each from self-help groups and Insurance Co-operative Societies:`
  line
  line `Provided that one of the representatives as mentioned in clause (a) shall be elected as the`
  line `Chairperson of the Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee of the General Insurance Council shall consist of the following persons,`
  line `namely: --`
  line
  line `(a) four representatives of members of the General Insurance Council elected in their individual`
  line `capacity by the members in such manner as may be laid down in the bye-laws of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) an eminent person not connected with insurance business, nominated by the Authority; and`
  line
  line `(c) four persons to represent insurance agents, third party administrators, surveyors and loss`
  line `assessors and policyholders respectively as may be nominated by the Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that one of the representatives as mentioned in clause (a) shall be elected as the`
  line `Chairperson of the Executive Committee of the General Insurance Council.`
  line
  line `(3) If anybody of persons specified in sub-sections (1) and (2) fails to elect any of the members of the`
  line `Executive Committees of the Life Insurance Council or the General Insurance Council, the Authority may`
  line `nominate any person to fill the vacancy, and any person so nominated shall be deemed to be a member of`
  line `the Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council or the General Insurance Council, as the case may`
  line `be, as if he had been duly elected thereto.`
  line
  line `(4) Each of the said Executive Committees may make bye-laws for the transaction of any business at`
  line `any meeting of the said Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The Life Insurance Council or the General Insurance Council may form such other committees`
  line `consisting of such persons as it may think fit to discharge such functions as may be delegated thereto.`
  line
  line `(6) The Secretary of the Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council and of the Executive`
  line `Committee of the General Insurance Council shall in each case be appointed by the Executive Committee`
  line `concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided that each Secretary appointed by the Executive Committee concerned shall exercise all such`
  line `powers and do all such acts as may be authorised in this behalf by the Executive Committee concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_g:
  sectionId (18228)
  sectionNo 64G
  orderNo 134
  title `Resignation and filling up of casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_g_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 73, for "by nomination by the Authority" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18228&sectionno=64G&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_g_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any member of the Executive`
  line `Committee of the Life Insurance Council or of the General Insurance Council may resign his membership`
  line `of the Committee by notice in writing addressed to the chairman of the Committee to that effect.`
  line
  line `(2) Casual vacancies in the Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council or of the General`
  line `Insurance Council, whether caused by resignation, death or otherwise, shall be filled ^1[in such manner as`
  line `may be laid down in the bye-laws of the Council concerned], and any person so nominated to fill the`
  line `vacancy shall hold office until the dissolution of the Committee to which he has been nominated.`
  line
  line `(3) No act of the Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council or of the General Insurance`
  line `Council shall be called in question on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy in, or defect in`
  line `the constitution of the Committee concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_h:
  sectionId (18229)
  sectionNo 64H
  orderNo 135
  title `Duration and dissolution of Executive Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18229&sectionno=64H&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_h_content:
  string
  line `(1) The duration of the Executive`
  line `Committee of the Life Insurance Council or the General Insurance Council shall be three years from the`
  line `date of its first meeting on the expiry of which it shall stand dissolved and a new Executive Committee`
  line constituted.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the dissolution of the Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council or the`
  line `General Insurance Council, the outgoing members thereof shall continue to hold office and discharge such administrative and other duties as may be prescribed until such time as a new Executive Committee`
  line `of the Life Insurance Council or the General Council, as the case may be, shall have been constituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_h_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64_i:
  sectionId (18230)
  sectionNo 64-I
  orderNo 136
  title Omitted..
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_i_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_i_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18230&sectionno=64-I&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_i_content:
  string
  line `[Power of Executive Committee of Life Insurance Councile to hold examinations for`
  line `insurance agents.] -- Omitted by Insurance Laws (Amendment) Act 2015 (5 of 2015) s. 74`
  line `(w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_64_i_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64_j:
  sectionId (18231)
  sectionNo 64J
  orderNo 137
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_j_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_j_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18231&sectionno=64J&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_j_content:
  string
  line `(1) The functions of the`
  line `Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council shall be--(a) to aid, advise and assist insurers`
  line `carrying on life insurance business in the matter of setting up standards of conduct and sound practice and`
  line `in the matter of rendering efficient service to holders of life insurance policies;`
  line
  line `(b) to render advice to the ^1[Authority] in the matter of controlling the expenses of insurers in`
  line `respect of their life insurance business in India;`
  line
  line `(c) to bring to the notice of the ^1[Authority] the case of any insurer acting in a manner prejudicial`
  line `to the interests of holders of life insurance policies;`
  line
  line `(d) to act in any matter incidental or ancillary to any of the matters specified in clauses (a) to (c)`
  line `as, with the approval of the ^2Authority], may be notified by the Life Insurance Council in the Gazette`
  line `of India.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) For the purpose of enabling it to effectively discharge its functions, the Executive Committee of`
  line `the Life Insurance Council may collect such fees as may be laid down in the bye-laws made by the`
  line `Council from the insurers carrying on life insurance business.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_j_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 30 and The First Schedule, ibid., for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 75, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_64_k:
  sectionId (18232)
  sectionNo 64K
  orderNo 138
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_k_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_k_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18232&sectionno=64K&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_k_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `It shall be the duty of the Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council to meet at least once before`
  line `the 31st day of March every year to advise the ^1[Authority] in fixing under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 40B the limits by which the actual expenses incurred by an insurer carrying on`
  line `life insurance business in respect of such business in the preceding year may exceed the limits prescribed`
  line `under that sub-section, and in fixing any such limits the`
  line `^1[Authority] shall have due regard to the`
  line `conditions obtaining in life insurance business generally during that year, and he may fix different groups`
  line `of insurers.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an insurer is guilty of contravening the provisions of section 40B with respect to the`
  line `expenses of management, the ^1[Authority] may, after giving the insurer an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `administer a warning to the insurer.`
  line
  line `(3) Where within a period of seven years two warnings have been given to an insurer under`
  line `sub-section (2) and they have been disregarded by hi m, the ^1[Authority] may cause an investigation and`
  line `valuation, as at such date as the ^1[Authority] may . specify, to be made at the expense of the insurer by an`
  line `actuary appointed by the insurer for this purpose and approved by the ^1[Authority], and the insurer shall`
  line `place at the disposal of the said actuary all the materials required by hi m for the purpose of such`
  line `investigation and valuation, within such period, not being less than three months, as the ^1[Authority] may`
  line specify.
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (1) and (4) of section 13 and of sub-sections (1) and (2) of`
  line `section 15, or, as the case may be, of sub-section (2) of section 16 shall apply in relation to an`
  line `investigation and valuation under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that the abstract and statement prepared as the result of such investigation and valuation`
  line `shall be furnished by such date as the ^2[Authority] may specify.`
  line
  line `(5) There shall be appended to every such abstract a statement signed by the actuary giving such`
  line `information as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) On receipt of the abstract and statement furnished in accordance with sub-section (4), the`
  line `^2[Authority] may take such action as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_k_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_64_l:
  sectionId (18233)
  sectionNo 64L
  orderNo 139
  title `Functions of Executive Committee of General Insurance Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_l_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_l_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18233&sectionno=64L&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_l_content:
  string
  line `(1) The functions of`
  line `the Executive Committee of the General Insurance Council shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to aid and advise insurers, carrying on general insurance business, in the matter of setting up`
  line `standards of conduct and sound practice and in the matter of rendering efficient service to holders of`
  line `policies of general insurance;`
  line
  line `(b) to render advice to the ^1[Authority] in the matter of controlling the expenses of such insurers`
  line `carrying on business in India in the matter of commission and other expenses;`
  line
  line `(c) to bring to the notice of the ^1[Authority] the case of any such insurer acting in a matter`
  line `prejudicial to the interests of holders of general insurance policies;`
  line
  line `(d) to act in any matter incidental or ancillary to any of the matters specified in clauses (a) to (c)`
  line `as with the approval of the ^2[Authority] may be notified by the General Insurance Council in the`
  line `Gazette of India.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) For the purpose of enabling it to effectively discharge its functions, the Executive Committee of`
  line `the General Insurance Council may collect such fees as may be laid down in the bye-laws made by the`
  line `Council from the insurers carrying on general insurance business.]`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that if the General Insurance Council thinks fit, it may by a resolution passed by it, waive`
  line `the collection of the prescribed fees for any year and where any such resolution has been approved by the`
  line `^2[Authority], the Executive Committee of the General Insurance Council shall not collect any fees in`
  line `relation to that year.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_l_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by ibid., s. 30 and the First Schedule (serial no. 2), for "Central Government (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 76, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by Act 62 of 1968, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-8-1939).`
obj_root_law_sections_64_m:
  sectionId (18234)
  sectionNo 64M
  orderNo 140
  title `Executive Committee of General Insurance Council may advise in controlling expenses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_m_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_m_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18234&sectionno=64M&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_m_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Executive Committee of the General Insurance Council to meet`
  line `at least once before the 31st day of March every year to advise the ^1[Authority] in fixing under the`
  line `proviso to sub-section (1) of section 40 C the limits by which the actual expenses of management incurred`
  line `by an insurer carrying on general insurance business in respect of such business in the preceding year may`
  line `exceed the limits prescribed under that sub-section, and in fixing any such limits the ^248`
  line `Authority shall`
  line `have due regard to the conditions obtaining in general insurance business in the preceding year, and he`
  line `may fix different limits for different groups of insurers.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an insurer is guilty of contravening the provisions of section 40C with respect to the`
  line `expenses of management the ^2[Authority] may, after giving the insurer an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `administer a warning to the insurer.`
  line
  line `(3) Where in any case two warnings given to an insurer under sub-section (2) have been disregarded`
  line `by hi m, the ^2[Authority] may take such action against the insurer as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_m_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_64_n:
  sectionId (18235)
  sectionNo 64N
  orderNo 141
  title `Power of the Executive Committees to act together in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_n_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 77, for "the Central Government may prescribe" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18235&sectionno=64N&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[The Authority may`
  line `specify] the circumstances in which, the manner in which, and the conditions subject to which, the`
  line `Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council and the Executive Committee of the General`
  line `Insurance Council may hold joint meetings for the purpose of dealing with any matter of common interest`
  line `to both Committees, and it shall be lawful for the two Committees at any such joint meeting to delegate`
  line `any matter under consideration for the determination of a sub-committee appointed for this purpose from`
  line `amongst the members of the two Committees.`
