obj_root_law_sections_64_r:
  sectionId (18239)
  sectionNo 64R
  orderNo 145
  title `General power of Life Insurance Council and General Insurance Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_r_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_r_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18239&sectionno=64R&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_r_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the`
  line `efficient performance of its duties, the Life Insurance Council or the General Insurance Council as the`
  line `case may be, may--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint such officers and servants as may be necessary and fix the conditions of their service;`
  line
  line `(b) determine the manner in which any prescribed fee may be collected;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) keep and maintain up-to-date, a copy of list of all insurers who are members of the either`
  line Council;]
  line
  line `(d)`
  line `^3[make bye-laws for] --`
  line
  line `(i) the holding of elections other than the first elections;`
  line
  line `(ii) the summoning and holding of meetings, the conduct of business thereat and the number of`
  line `persons necessary to form a quorum;`
  line
  line `(iii) the submission by insurers to the Executive Committee of the Life Insurance Council, or the`
  line `General Insurance Council, of such statements or information as may be required of them and the`
  line `submission of copies thereof by the insurers to the ^1[Authority];`
  line
  line `(iv) the levy and collection of any fees;`
  line
  line `(v) the regulation of any other matter which may be necessary for the purpose of enabling it to`
  line `carry out its duties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Life Insurance Council or the General Insurance Council may authorise the Executive`
  line `Committee concerned ^4*** to exercise any of the powers conferred on the Life Insurance Council or the`
  line `General Insurance Council, as the case may be, under clause (a), clause (b) , clause (c) of sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_64_r_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for "with the previous approval of the Authority make regulations for" (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `4. The words "or the Tariff Committee appointed under section 64-O" omitted by Act 62 of 1968, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-6-1969).`
