obj_root_law_sections_64_ula_content:
  string
  line `^1[64ULA. Transitional provisions. --(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Part, until the`
  line `rates, advantage and terms and conditions laid down by the Advisory Committee under section 64UC are`
  line `de-notified by the Authority with effect from such date as the Authority may by notification in the Official Gazette determine, and the rates, advantages and terms and conditions are decided by the insurer`
  line `concerned, the rates, advantages and terms and conditions notified by the Advisory Committee shall`
  line `continue to be in force and shall always be deemed to have been in force and any such rates, advantages`
  line `and terms and conditions shall be binding on all the insurers.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall, in consultation with the Central Government, prepare a scheme for the`
  line `existing employees of the Tariff Advisory Committee on its dissolution, keeping in view the interests of`
  line `such employees on such terms and conditions as it may, by order, determine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_um:
  sectionId (18256)
  sectionNo 64UM
  orderNo 162
  title `Surveyors and loss assessors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_um_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 82, for section 64UM (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18256&sectionno=64UM&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_um_content:
  string
  line `^1[64UM. Surveyors or loss assessors. --(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, no person`
  line `shall act as a surveyor or loss assessor in respect of general insurance business after the expiry of a period`
  line `of one year from the commencement of the Insurance Laws (Amendment) Act, 2015 (5 of 2015), unless`
  line he--
  line
  line `(a) possesses such academic qualifications as may be specified by the regulations made under this`
  line `Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) is a member of a professional body of surveyors and loss assessors, namely, the Indian`
  line `Institute of Insurance Surveyors and Loss Assessors:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a firm or company, all the partners or directors or other persons, who`
  line `may be called upon to make a survey or assess a loss reported, as the case may be, shall fulfill the`
  line `requirements of clauses (a) and (b).`
  line
  line `(2) Every surveyor and loss assessor shall comply with the code of conduct in respect of his duties,`
  line `responsibilities and other professional requirements, as may be specified by the regulations made under`
  line `the Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions, a class or class of persons acting`
  line `as a licensed surveyor or loss assessor prior to the commencement of the Insurance Laws (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 2015 (5 of 2015) shall continue to act as such for such period as may be specified by the regulations`
  line `made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the surveyor or loss assessor shall, within the period as may be notified by the`
  line `Authority, satisfy the requirements of clause (a) and clause (b) of sub-section (1), failing which, the`
  line `surveyor or loss assessor shall be automatically disqualified to act as a surveyor or loss assessor.`
  line
  line `(4) No claim in respect of a loss which has occurred in India and requiring to be paid or settled in`
  line `India equal to or exceeding an amount specified in the regulations by the Authority in value on any policy`
  line `of insurance, arising or intimated to an insurer at any time after the expiry of a period of one year from`
  line `the commencement of the Insurance Laws (Amendment) Act, 2015 (5 of 2015), shall, unless otherwise`
  line `directed by the Authority, be admitted for payment or settled by the insurer unless he has obtained a`
  line `report, on the loss that has occurred, from a person who holds a licence issued under this section to act as`
  line `a surveyor or loss assessor (hereafter referred to as "approved surveyor or loss assessor"):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to take away or abridge the right of the`
  line `insurer to pay or settle any claim at any amount different from the amount assessed by the approved`
  line `surveyor or loss assessor.`
  line
  line `(5) The Authority may, at any time, in respect of any claim of the nature referred to in sub-section (4),`
  line `call for an independent report from any other approved surveyor or loss assessor specified by him and`
  line `such surveyor or loss assessor shall furnish such report to the Authority within such time as may be`
  line `specified by the Authority or if no time limit has been specified by him within a reasonable time and the`
  line `cost of, or incidental to, such report shall be borne by the insurer.`
  line
  line `(6) The Authority may, on receipt of a report referred to in sub-section (5), issue such directions as it`
  line `may consider necessary with regard to the settlement of the claim including any direction to settle a claim`
  line `at a figure less than, or more than, that at which it is proposed to settle it or it was settled and the insurer`
  line `shall be bound to comply with such directions:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Authority issues a direction for settling a claim at a figure lower than that at`
  line `which it has already been settled, the insurer shall be deemed to comply with such direction if he satisfies`
  line `the Authority that all reasonable steps, with due regard to the question whether the expenditure involved`
  line `is not disproportionate to the amount required to be recovered, have been taken with due dispatch by him:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no direction for the payment of a lesser sum shall be made where the amount of`
  line `the claim has already been paid and the Authority is of opinion that the recovery of the amount paid in`
  line `excess would cause undue hardship to the insured:`
  line
  line `Provided also that nothing in this section shall relieve the insurer from any liability, civil or criminal,`
  line `to which he would have been subject but for the provisions of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(7) No insurer shall, after the expiry of a period of one year from the commencement of the Insurance`
  line `Laws (Amendment) Act, 2015 (5 of 2015) pay to any person any fee or remuneration for surveying,`
  line `verifying or reporting on a claim of loss under a policy of insurance unless the person making such`
  line `survey, verification or report is an approved surveyor or loss assessor.`
  line
  line `(8) Where, in the case of a claim of less than the amount specified in sub-section (4) in value on any`
  line `policy of insurance it is not practicable for an insurer to employ an approved surveyor or loss assessor`
  line `without incurring expenses disproportionate to the amount of the claim, the insurer may employ any other`
  line `person (not being a person disqualified for the time being for being employed as a surveyor or loss`
  line `assessor) for surveying such loss and may pay such reasonable fee or remuneration to the person so`
  line `employed as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(9) The Authority may in respect of any claim of value of less than the amount specified in`
  line `sub-section (4) on an insurance policy, if the claim has not been or is not proposed to be reported upon by`
  line `a surveyor or loss assessor, direct that such claim shall be reported upon by an approved surveyor or loss`
  line `assessor and where the Authority makes such direction, the provisions of sub-sections (5) and (6) shall`
  line `apply in respect of such claim.`
  line
  line `(10) Where, in relation to any class of claims, the Authority is satisfied that it is customary to entrust`
  line `the work of survey or loss assessment to any person other than a licensed surveyor or loss assessor, or it is`
  line `not practicable to make any survey or loss assessment, it may, by an order, exempt such class of claims`
  line `from the operation of this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_v:
  sectionId (18257)
  sectionNo 64V
  orderNo 163
  title `Assets and liabilities how to be valued.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_v_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 83, for sections 64V and 64VA (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18257&sectionno=64V&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_v_content:
  string
  line `^1[64V. Assets and liabilities how to be valued. --(1) For the purpose of ascertaining compliance`
  line `with the provisions of section 64VA, assets shall be valued at value not exceeding their market or`
  line `realisable value and certain assets may be excluded by the Authority in the manner as may be specified by`
  line `the regulations made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) A proper value shall be placed on every item of liability of the insurer in the manner as may be`
  line `specified by the regulations made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Every insurer shall furnish to the Authority along with the returns required to be filed under this`
  line `Act, a statement, certified by an Auditor, approved by the Authority, in respect of general insurance`
  line `business or an actuary approved by the Authority in respect of life insurance business, as the case may be,`
  line `of his assets and liabilities assessed in the manner required by this section as on the 31st day of March of`
  line `each year within such time as may be specified by the regulations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_va:
  sectionId (18258)
  sectionNo 64VA
  orderNo 164
  title `Sufficiency of assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_va_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 83, for sections 64V and 64VA (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18258&sectionno=64VA&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_va_content:
  string
  line `^1[64VA. Sufficiency of assets. --(1) Every insurer and re-insurer shall at all times maintain an excess`
  line `of value of assets over the amount of liabilities of, not less than fifty per cent. of the amount of minimum`
  line `capital as stated under section 6 and arrived at in the manner specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) An insurer or re-insurer, as the case may be, who does not comply with sub-section (1), shall be`
  line `deemed to be insolvent and may be wound-up by the court on an application made by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall by way of regulation made for the purpose, specify a level of solvency margin`
  line `known as control level of solvency on the breach of which the Authority shall act in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (4) without prejudice to taking of any other remedial measures as deemed fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that if in respect of any insurer the Authority is satisfied that either by reason of an`
  line `unfavourable claim experience or because of a sharp increase in the volume of new business, or for any`
  line `other reason, compliance with the provisions of this sub-section shall cause undue hardship to the insurer,`
  line `it may direct that for such period and subject to such conditions as it may specify, the provisions of this`
  line `sub-section shall apply to that insurer with such modifications provided that such modifications shall not`
  line `result in the control level of solvency being less than what is stipulated under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) If, at any time, an insurer or re-insurer does not maintain the required control level of solvency`
  line `margin, he shall, in accordance with the directions issued by the Authority, submit a financial plan to the`
  line `Authority, indicating a plan of action to correct the deficiency within a specified period not exceeding six`
  line months.
  line
  line `(5) An insurer who has submitted a plan, as required under sub-section (4), the Authority shall`
  line `propose modifications to the plan, if the Authority considers the same inadequate, and in such an`
  line `eventuality, the Authority shall give directions, as may be deemed necessary, including direction in regard`
  line `to transacting any new business, or, appointment of an administrator or both.`
  line
  line `(6) An insurer or re-insurer, as the case may be, who does not comply with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (4) shall be deemed to have made default in complying with the requirements of this section.`
  line
  line `(7) The Authority shall be entitled at any time to take such steps as it may consider necessary for the`
  line `inspection or verification of the assets and liabilities of any insurer or re-insurer, or for securing the`
  line `particulars necessary to establish that the requirements of this section have been complied with as on any`
  line `date, and the insurer or re-insurer, as the case may be, shall comply with any requisition made in this`
  line `behalf by the Authority, and in the event of any failure to do so within two months from the receipt of the`
  line `requisition, the insurer or re-insurer, as the case may be, shall be deemed to have made default in`
  line `complying with the requirements of this section.`
  line
  line `(8) In applying the provisions of sub-section (1) to any insurer or re-insurer, as the case may be, who`
  line `is a member of a group, the relevant amount for that insurer shall be an amount equal to that proportion of`
  line `the relevant amount which that group, if considered as a single insurer, would have been required to`
  line `maintain as the proportion of his share of the risk on each policy issued by the group bears to the total risk`
  line `on that policy:`
  line
  line `Provided that when a group of insurers ceases to be a group, every insurer in that group who`
  line `continues to carry on any class of insurance business in India shall comply with the requirements of subsection`
  line `(1) as if he had not been an insurer in a group at any time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that it shall be sufficient compliance of the provisions of the foregoing proviso if the`
  line `insurer brings up the excess of the value of his assets over the amount of his liabilities to the required`
  line `amount within a period of six months from the date of cessation of the group:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Authority may, on sufficient cause being shown, extend the said period of six`
  line `months by such further periods as it may think fit, so, however that the total period may not in any case`
  line `exceed one year.`
  line
  line `(9) Every insurer shall furnish to the Authority return giving details of solvency margin in such form,`
  line `time, manner including its authentication as may be specified by the regulations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_vb:
  sectionId (18259)
  sectionNo 64VB
  orderNo 165
  title `No risk to be assumed unless premium is received in advance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_vb_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2002, s. 13 (w.e.f. 23-9-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18259&sectionno=64VB&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_vb_content:
  string
  line `(1) No insurer shall`
  line `assume any risk in India in respect of any insurance business on which premium is not ordinarily payable`
  line `outside India unless and until the premium payable is received by him or is guaranteed to be paid by such`
  line `person in such manner and within such time as may be prescribed or unless and until deposit of such`
  line `amount as may be prescribed, is made in advance in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, in the case of risks for which premium can be ascertained in`
  line `advance, the risk may be assumed not earlier than the date on which the premium has been paid in cash or`
  line `by cheque to the insurer.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --Where the premium is tendered by postal money order or cheque sent by post, the`
  line `risk may be assumed on the date on which the money order is booked or the cheque is posted, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Any refund of premium which may become due to an insured on account of the cancellation of a`
  line `policy or alteration in its terms and conditions or otherwise shall be paid by the insurer directly to the`
  line `insured by a crossed or order cheque or by postal money order and a proper receipt shall be obtained by`
  line `the insurer from the insured, and such refund shall in no case be credited to the account of the agent.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an insurance agent collects a premium on a policy of insurance on behalf of an insurer, he`
  line `shall deposit with, or dispatch by post to, the insurer, the premium so collected in full without deduction`
  line `of his commission within twenty-four hours of the collection excluding bank and postal holidays.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, by rules, relax the requirements of sub-section (1) in respect of`
  line `particular categories in insurance policies.`
  line
  line `^1[(6) The Authority may, from time to time, specify, by the regulations made by it, the manner of`
  line `receipt of premium by the insurer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_vc:
  sectionId (18260)
  sectionNo 64VC
  orderNo 166
  title `Restrictions on the opening of a new place of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_vc_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 84, for section 64VC (26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18260&sectionno=64VC&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_64_vc_content:
  string
  line `^1[64VC. Restrictions on opening of new place of business.--No insurer shall, after the`
  line `commencement of the Insurance (Amendment) Act, 1968 (62 of 1968), open a new place of business or`
  line `close a place in India or outside India or change otherwise than within the same city, town or village, the`
  line `location of an existing place of business situated in India or outside India, except in the manner as may be`
  line `specified by the regulations.]`
