obj_root_law_sections_110_ha_content:
  string
  line `^1[110HA. Penalty to be recoverable as arrear of land revenue. -- Any penalty imposed by the`
  line `Authority under this Act shall be recoverable as an arrear of land revenue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (18332)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 239
  title `Service of notices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18332&sectionno=111&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any process or notice required to be served on an insurer ^1*** shall be`
  line `sufficiently served if addressed to any person registered with the ^2[Authority] as a person authorised to`
  line `accept notices on behalf of the insurer ^1*** and left at, or sent by registered post to the address of such`
  line `person as registered with the ^2[Authority].`
  line
  line `(2) Any notice or other document which is by this Act required to be sent to any policy-holder may be`
  line `addressed and sent to the person to whom notices respecting such policy are usually sent and any notice`
  line `so addressed and sent shall be deemed to be notice to the holder of such policy:`
  line
  line `Provided, that, where any person claiming to be interested in a policy as transferee, assignee or`
  line `nominee has given to an insurer ^3*** notice in writing of his interest, any notice which is by this Act`
  line `required to be sent to policy-holders shall also be sent to such person at the address specified by him`
  line `in his notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or provident society" omitted by s. 98, ibid. (w.e.f. 26.12.2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `3. The words "or to a provident society" omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 98 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (18333)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 240
  title `Declaration of interium bonuses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18333&sectionno=112&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this`
  line `Act, an insurer carrying on the business of life insurance shall be at liberty to declare an interim bonus or`
  line `bonuses to policy-holders whose policies mature for payment by reason of death or otherwise during the`
  line `intervaluation period on the recommendation of the investigating of actuary made at the last preceding`
  line valuation.
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (18334)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 241
  title `Acquisition of surrender value by policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 99, ibid., for section 113 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18334&sectionno=113&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `^1[113. Acquisition of surrender value by policy. --(1) A policy of life insurance shall acquire`
  line `surrender value as per the norms specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Every policy of life insurance shall contain the formula as approved by the Authority for`
  line `calculation of guaranteed surrender value of the policy.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding any contract to the contrary, a policy of life insurance under a non-linked plan`
  line `which has acquired a surrender value shall not lapse by reason of non-payment of further premiums but`
  line `shall be kept in force to the extent of paid-up sum insured, calculated by means of a formula as approved`
  line `by the Authority and contained in the policy and the reversionary bonuses that have already been attached`
  line `to the policy:`
  line
  line `Provided that a policy of life insurance under a linked plan shall be kept in force in the manner as`
  line `may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-section (3) shall not apply--`
  line
  line `(i) where the paid-up sum insured by a policy, inclusive of attached bonuses, is less than the`
  line `amount specified by the Authority or takes the form of annuity of amount less than the amount`
  line `specified by the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(ii) when the parties, after the default has occurred in payment of the premium, agree in writing to`
  line `other arrangement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (18335)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 242
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18335&sectionno=114&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, subject to`
  line `the condition of previous publication by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line prescribe--
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3[(aaa) t the conditions and manner of foreign investment under sub-clause (b) of clause (7A) of`
  line `section 2;]`
  line
  line `^4[(b) the manner in which it shall be determined which of the transactions of an insurer are to be`
  line `deemed for the purposes of this Act to be insurance business transacted ^5*** in ^6[India] ^7***;]`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) the form referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which the prospectuses and tables referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 41 shall be published and the form in which they shall be drawn up;`
  line
  line `^9* * * * *`
  line
  line `^10* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) the contingencies other than those specified in clauses (a) to (f) of ^11[sub-section (2) of]`
  line `section 65 on the happening of which money may be paid by provident societies;`
  line
  line `(i) the matters other than those specified in clauses (a) to (o) of sub-section (1) of section 74 on`
  line `which a provident society shall make rules;`
  line
  line `(j) the form of any account, return or registered required by the Part III and the manner in which`
  line `such account, return or register shall be verified;`
  line
  line `(k) subject to the provisions of this Act, the fees payable thereunder and the manner in which they`
  line `are to be collected; ^12***.`
  line
  line `(l) the conditions and the matters which may be prescribed under sub-sections (5), ^13[(6)], (10) and`
  line `(12) of section 92;`
  line
  line `^14[(la) the manner of inquiry under sub-section (l) of section 105C;`
  line
  line `(lb) the form in which an appeal may be preferred under sub-section (2) and the fee payable in`
  line `respect of such appeal and the procedure for filing and disposing of an appeal under sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 110;]`
  line
  line `^15* * * * *`
  line
  line `^16[(m) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^17* * * * *`
  line
  line `^18[(3) Every rule made under this section or under sub-section (10) of section 34H ^19*** and every`
  line `regulation made under this Part shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of`
  line `Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule or regulation.]`
  line
  line `^20[(4)] All rules made by a Local Government under the provisions of section 24 of the Provident`
  line `Insurance Societies Act, 1912 (5 of 1912) and in force at the commencement of this Act shall so far as not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of Part III continue in force and have effect as if duly made under this`
  line `section until they are replaced by rules made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (a) omitted by Act 42 of 2002, s. 16 (w.e.f. 23-9-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (aa) omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 100 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 6 of 2021, s. 4, for clause (aaa) (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 1941, s. 62, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 8-4-1941).`
  line
  line `5. The words in India or omitted by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid., for the States (w.e.f. 1-11-1956)`
  line
  line `7. The words as the case may be omitted by Act s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `8. Clause (c) omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 100 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `9. Clause (f) omitted by s. 100, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `10. Clause (g) omitted by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 20 of 1940, s. 16 (w.e.f. 10-4-1940).`
  line
  line `12. The word and omitted by Act 20 of 1940, s. 16 (w.e.f. 10-4-1940).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 11 of 1939, s. 32.`
  line
  line `14. Ins. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 100 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `15. Clause (ll) omitted by Act 41 of 1999, s. 30 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `16. Ins. by Act 20 of 1940, s. 16 (w.e.f. 10-4-1940).`
  line
  line `17. The proviso omitted by ibid, s. 16 (w.e.f. 10-4-1940).`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  line
  line `19. The words, brackets, figures and letters or under sub-section (1) of section 64UB and every regulation made under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 64UB omitted by Act 5 of 2015, s. 100 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `20@. Sub-section (3) re-numbered as sub-section (4) thereof by Act 20 of 1940, s. 16 (w.e.f. 10-4-1940).`
obj_root_law_sections_114_a:
  sectionId (18336)
  sectionNo 114A
  orderNo 243
  title `Power of Authority to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525&sectionId=18336&sectionno=114A&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00044_193804_1523351752525
obj_root_law_sections_114_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[114A. Power of Authority to make regulations.--(1) The Authority may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder, to carry out the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: --`
  line
  line `^2[(a) manner of making application for registration and documents to be accompanied under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 3;]`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of suspension or cancellation of registration under sub-section (5E) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) such fee, not exceeding five thousand rupees, as may be determined by the regulations for`
  line `issue of a duplicate certificate of registration under subsection (7) of section 3;`
  line
  line `^3[(d) such annual fee to the Authority and manner of payment under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 3A;]
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(da) such minimum annuity and other benefits to be secured by the insurer under section 4;`
  line
  line `(daa) determination of preliminary expenses that may be excluded for calculation of the`
  line `stipulated paid-up equity capital for the insurers under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(db) such equity capital and such forms of capital including hybrid capital required under`
  line `sub-section (I) of section 6A;]`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4[(ea) separation of account of all receipts and payments in respect of each classes and`
  line `sub-classes of insurance business as required under sub-section (1) and sub-section (2AA) of section`
  line `10; and its waiver under the said section;]`
  line
  line `(f) the preparation of balance-sheet, profit and loss account and a separate account of receipts and`
  line `payments and revenue account ^6[under sub-section (1) of section 11];`
  line
  line `^7[(g) the manner in which an abstract of the report of the actuary to be specified and the form and`
  line `manner in which the statement referred to in section 13 shall be appended;]`
  line
  line `^4[(ga) maintenance of records of policies and claims under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(gb) manner and form of issuance of policies in electronic form under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 14;]`
  line
  line `^8[(h) the fee for procuring a copy of return or any part thereof under sub-section (I) of`
  line `section 20;]`
  line
  line `^9[(i) investment of assets and further provisions regarding investments by an insurer and`
  line `investment by insurers in certain cases under sections 27, 27A, 27B, 27C and time, manner and other`
  line `conditions of investment of assets under section 27D;]`
  line
  line `^10[(ia) the form in which a return giving details of investments made, time and manner including`
  line `its authentication under section 28;`
  line
  line `(ib) the loans including the loans sanctioned to the full-time employees of the insurer under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(ic) the sum to be paid by the insurer to any person under section 31B;`
  line
  line `(id) the obligation of insurer in respect of rural or social or unorganised sector and backward`
  line `classes under sections 32B and 32C;`
  line
  line `(ie) the minimum percentage of insurance business in third party risks of motor vehicles under`
  line `section 32D;]`
  line
  line `^11[(j) the minimum information to be maintained by insurers or intermediary or insurance`
  line `intermediary, as the case may be, in their books, the manner in which such information shall be`
  line `maintained, the checks and other verifications in that connection and all other matters incidental`
  line `thereto under sub-section (7) of section 33;]`
  line
  line `^12[(ja) the form in which balance-sheets in respect of the insurance business of each of the insurers`
  line `concerned and the manner in which actuarial reports and abstracts in respect of the life insurance`
  line `business are to be prepared under clauses (b) and (c) of sub-section (3) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(jb) the manner of assessment of compensation under the proviso to sub-section (4A) of`
  line `section 37A;`
  line
  line `(jc) the fee to be charged by the insurer under sub-section (3) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(jd) the manner and amount of remuneration or reward to be paid or received by way of`
  line `commission or otherwise to an insurance agent or an intermediary or insurance intermediary under`
  line `section 40;`
  line
  line `(je) the manner and form of expenses of management under sections 40B and 40C;]`
  line
  line `^13* * * * *`
  line
  line `^14* * * * *`
  line
  line `^15[(m) the requisite qualifications or practical training or examination to be passed for appointment`
  line `as an insurance agent under clause (e) of sub-section (3) of section 42;]`
  line
  line `^16* * * * *`
  line
  line `^17[(o) the code of conduct under clause (h) of sub-section (3) of section 42;]`
  line
  line `^18* * * * *]`
  line
  line `(q) the manner and the fees for issue of a licence to an intermediary or an insurance intermediary`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 42D;`
  line
  line `(r) the fee and the additional fee to be determined for renewal of licence of intermediaries or`
  line `insurance intermediaries under sub-section (3) of section 42D;`
  line
  line `(s) the requisite qualifications and practical training of intermediaries or insurance intermediaries`
  line `under clause (e) of sub-section (5) of section 42D;`
  line
  line `(t) the examination to be passed to act as an intermediary or insurance intermediary under`
  line `clause (f) of sub-section (5) of section 42D;`
  line
  line `(u) the code of conduct under clause (g) of sub-section (5) of section 42D;`
  line
  line `(v) the fee for issue of duplicate licence under sub-section (7) of section 42D;`
  line
  line ^19[
  line `^20* * * * *`
  line
  line `(vb) the requirements of capital, form of business and other conditions to act as an intermediary`
  line `or insurance intermediary under ^21*** section 42E;`
  line
  line `(vc) the form of balance-sheet, as may be specified by the Authority under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 49;]`
  line
  line `^22* * * * *`
  line
  line `^23[(x) academic qualifications and code of conduct for surveyors and loss assessors under`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 64UM;`
  line
  line `(xa) the period for which a person may act as a surveyor or loss assessor under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 64UM;]`
  line
  line `^24[(y) the manner of exclusion of certain assets under sub-section (1), the manner of valuation of`
  line `liabilities under sub-section (2) and time for furnishing statement under sub-section (3) of section`
  line 64V;]
  line
  line `(z) the valuation of assets and liabilities under sub-section (3) of section 64V;`
  line
  line `^25[(za) the matters specified under sub-section (1) of section 64VA relating to sufficiency of`
  line assets;]
  line
  line `(zaa) the manner of receipt of premium to be specified under sub-section (6) of section 64VB;]`
  line
  line `^26[(zab) the form, time, manner including authentication of the return giving details of solvency`
  line `margin under sub-section (9) of section 64VA;`
  line
  line `(zac) the manner of opening and closing places of business under section 64VC;]`
  line
  line `(zb) the matters relating to re-insurance under sections 101A and 101B;`
  line
  line `^27[(zba) the norms for surrender value of life insurance policy under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 113;]`
  line
  line `(zc) the matters relating to redressal of grievances of policy-holders to protect their interest and to`
  line `regulate, promote and ensure orderly growth of insurance industry; and`
  line
  line `(zd) any other matter which is to be, or may be, specified by the regulations made by the`
  line `Authority or in respect of which provision is to be made or may be made by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
